obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (37599)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338&sectionId=37599&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the ^1*** Registration Act,`
  line 1908.
  line
  line `^2[(2) It extends to the whole of India ^3***:`
  line
  line `Provided that the State Government may exclude any districts or tracts of country from its operation.]`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on the first day of January, 1909.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line Karnataka
  line
  line `Amendment of section 1.--For sub-section (3) of section 1 of the Registration (Karnataka`
  line `Amendment) Act, 1976 (Karnataka Act 55 of 1976) the following sub-section shall be and shall be`
  line `deemed have been substituted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"(3) This section and sections 3, 13, 14, 16, 17 and 19 shall come into force at once and the other`
  line `sections shall come into force on such date as the State Government may, by notification, appoint and`
  line `different sections areas."`
  line
  line `[Vide Karnataka Act 64 of 1976, s. 2]`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The word "Indian" omitted by Act 45 of 1969, s. 2.`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 3 of 1951, s. 3 and the Schedule, for sub-section (2)`
  line
  line `3. The words "except the State of Jammu and Kashmir" omitted by Act 34 of 2019, s. 95 and the Fifth Schedule (w.e.f. 31-10-`
  line `2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (37600)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338&sectionId=37600&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless there is anything repugnant in the subject or context,--`
  line
  line `(1) "Addition" means the place of residence, and the profession, trade, rank and title (if any) of a`
  line `person described, and in the case of ^1[an Indian], ^2*** his father's name, or where he is usually`
  line `described as the son of his mother, then his mother's name;`
  line
  line `(2) "Book" includes a portion of a book and also any number of sheets connected together with a`
  line `view of forming a book or portion of a book;`
  line
  line `(3) "District" and "sub-district" respectively mean a district and sub-district formed under this`
  line Act;
  line
  line `(4) "District Court" includes the High Court in its ordinary original civil jurisdiction;`
  line
  line `(5) "Endorsement" and "endorsed" include and apply to an entry in writing by a registering`
  line `officer on a rider or covering slip to any document tendered for registration under this Act;`
  line
  line `(6) "Immovable Property" includes land, buildings, hereditary allowances, rights to ways, lights,`
  line `ferries, fisheries or any other benefit to arise out of land, and things attached to the earth, or`
  line `permanently fastened to anything which is attached to the earth, but not standing timber, growing`
  line `crops nor grass;`
  line
  line `^3[(6A) "India" means the territory of India excluding the State of Jammu and Kashmir;[`
  line
  line `(7) "Lease" includes a counterpart, kabuliyat, and undertaking to cultivate or occupy, and an`
  line `agreement to lease;`
  line
  line `(8) "Minor" means a person who, according to the personal law to which he is subject, has not`
  line `attained majority;`
  line
  line `(9) "Movable Property" includes standing timber, growing crops and grass, fruit upon and juice`
  line `in trees, and property of every other description, except immovable property; and`
  line
  line `(10) "Representative" includes the guardian of a minor and the committee or other legal curator`
  line `of a lunatic or idiot.`
  line
  line `^4* * * * *`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by A.O. 1950, for "a Native of India".`
  line
  line `2. The words and brackets "his cast (if any) and" omitted by Act 17 of 1956, s. 2.`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 3 of 1951, s. 3 and the Schedule.`
  line
  line `4. Clause (11) omitted by Act 3 of 1951, s. 3 and Schedule. Earlier it was inserted by the A.O. 1950.`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (37601)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Inspector-General of Registration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338&sectionId=37601&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) The ^1[State Government] shall appoint an officer to be`
  line `the Inspector-General of Registration for the territories subject to such Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that the ^1[State Government] may, instead of making such appointment, direct that all or any`
  line `of the powers and duties hereinafter conferred and imposed upon the Inspector-General shall be exercised`
  line `and performed by such officer or officers, and within such local limits, as the ^1[State Government]`
  line `appoints in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(2) Any Inspector-General may hold simultaneously any other office under the ^2[Government].`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for "Provincial Government".`
  line
  line `2. Subs., ibid., for "the Crown".`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (37602)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title [Repealed.].
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338&sectionId=37602&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `[Branch Inspector-General of Sindh (Repealed).]--Rep. by the Government of India (Adaptation of`
  line `Indian Laws) Order, 1937.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (37603)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Districts and sub-districts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338&sectionId=37603&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) For the purposes of this Act, the ^1[State Government] shall form`
  line `districts and sub-districts, and shall prescribe, and may alter, the limits of such districts and sub-districts.`
  line
  line `(2) The districts and sub-districts formed under this section, together with the limits thereof, and`
  line `every alternation of such limits, shall be notified in the ^2[Official Gazette].`
  line
  line `(3) Every such alternation shall take effect on such day after the date of the notification as is therein`
  line mentioned
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for "Provincial Government".`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "Local Official Gazette"`
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (37604)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Registrars and Sub-Registrars.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338&sectionId=37604&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `The ^1[State Government] may appoint such persons, whether`
  line `public officers or not, as it thinks proper, to be Registrars of the several districts, and to be Sub-Registrars`
  line `of the several sub-districts, formed as aforesaid, respectively.`
  line
  line `^2* * * * *`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line Karnataka
  line
  line `Amendment of section 6.--In section 6 of the Registration Act, 1908 (Central Act 16 of 1908) the`
  line `following provisos inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"Provided that the State Government may also appoint one or more Sub-Registrars for the same`
  line `Sub-District:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the State Government may delegate to the Inspector-General of`
  line `Registration, the power of appointing Sub-Registrars."`
  line
  line `[Vide Karnataka Act 32 of 2001, s. 2]`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for Provincial Government.`
  line
  line `2. The proviso rep. by the A.O. 1937. Earlier it was inserted by Act 4 of 1914, s. 2 and the Schedule.`
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (37605)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Offices of Registrar and Sub-Registrar.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for "Provincial Government".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338&sectionId=37605&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) The ^1[State Government] shall establish in every`
  line `district an office to be styled the office of the Registrar and in every sub-district an office or offices to be`
  line `styled the office of the Sub-Registrar or the offices of the Joint Sub-Registrars.`
  line
  line `(2) The ^1[State Government] may amalgamate with any office of a Registrar, any office of a`
  line `Sub-Registrar subordinate to such Registrar, and may authorise any Sub-Registrar whose office has been`
  line `so amalgamated to exercise and perform, in addition to his own powers and duties, all or any of the`
  line `powers and the duties of the Registrar to whom he is subordinate:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such authorisation shall enable a Sub-Registrar to hear an appeal against an order`
  line `passed by himself under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (37606)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Inspectors of Registration offices.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for "Provincial Government".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338&sectionId=37606&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) The ^1`
  line `[State Government] may also appoint officers to be`
  line `called Inspector of Registration offices, and may prescribe the duties of such officers.`
  line
  line `(2) Every such Inspector shall be subordinate to the Inspector-General.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line Orissa
  line
  line `Amendment of section 8.--In section 8 of the Registration Act, 1908 (16 of 1908) (hereinafter`
  line `referred to as the principal Act),--`
  line
  line `(a) in sub-section (1), for the words " Inspector of Registration Offices" the words " Additional`
  line `Inspector –General of Registration, Joint Inspector-General of Registration and Deputy InspectorGeneral of Registration" shall be substituted; and`
  line
  line `(b) in sub-section(2), for the words "Inspector", the words "Additional Inspector-General, Joint`
  line `Inspector-General and Deputy Inspector-General" shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Orissa Act 8 of 2002, s. 2]`
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (37607)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title [Repealed.].
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338&sectionId=37607&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `[Military cantonments may be declared sub-districts or districts (Repealed).] Rep. by the Repealing`
  line `and Amending Act, 1927 (10 of 1927), s. 3 and Second Schedule.]`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (37608)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Absence of Registrar or vacancy in his office.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for "Provincial Government".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338&sectionId=37608&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) When any Registrar, other than the`
  line `Registrar of a district including a Presidency-town, is absent otherwise than on duty in his district, or`
  line `when his office is temporarily vacant, any person whom the Inspector-General appoints in this behalf, or,`
  line `in default of such appointment, the Judge of the District Court within the local limits of whose`
  line `jurisdiction the Registrar's office is situate, shall be the Registrar during such absence or until the ^1[State`
  line `Government] fills up the vacancy.`
  line
  line `(2) When the Registrar of a district including a Presidency-town is absent otherwise than on duty in`
  line `his district, or when his office is temporarily vacant, any person whom the Inspector-General appoints in`
  line `this behalf shall be the Registrar during such absence, or until the ^1[State Government] fills up the`
  line vacancy.
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (37609)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Absence of Registrar on duty in his district.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338&sectionId=37609&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `When any Registrar is absent from his office on`
  line `duty in his district, he may appoint any Sub-Registrar or other person in his district to perform, during`
  line `such absence, all the duties of a Registrar except those mentioned in sections 68 and 72.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (37610)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Absence of Sub-Registrar or vacancy in his office.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 4 of 1914, s. 2 and the Schedule, for "the Local Government fills up the vacancy".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338&sectionId=37610&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `When any Sub-Registrar is absent, or`
  line `when his office is temporarily vacant, any person whom the Registrar of the district appoints in this`
  line `behalf shall be Sub-Registrar during such absence, or until ^1[the vacancy is filled up].`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line Karnataka
  line
  line `Amendment of section 12.--In section 12, after the word "whom" the words "the Inspector-General of`
  line `Registration or" shall be inserted.]`
  line
  line `[Vide Karnataka Act 32 of 2001, s. 3]`
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (37611)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Report to State Government of appointments under sections 10, 11 and 12.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338&sectionId=37611&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1)`
  line `^2*** All`
  line `appointments made under section 10, section 11 or section 12 shall be reported to the ^1[State`
  line `Government] by the Inspector-General.`
  line `(2) Such report shall be either special or general, as the ^1]State Government directs.`
  line
  line `^3* * * * *`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for "Provincial Government"`
  line
  line `2. The words and figure "All appointments made by the Inspector-General section 6 and" rep. by the A.O. 1937. Earlier these`
  line `words and figure were ins. by Act 4 of 1914, s. 2 and the Schedule.`
  line
  line `3. Sub-section (3) rep. by the A.O. 1937.`
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (37612)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Establishments of registering officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338&sectionId=37612&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line ^2***
  line
  line `(2) The ^1[State Government] may allow proper establishments for the several offices under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for "Provincial Government"`
  line
  line `2. Sub-section (1) rep., ibid.,`
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (37613)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Seal of registering officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for "Provincial Government".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338&sectionId=37613&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `The several Registrars and Sub-Registrars shall use a seal bearing`
  line `the following inscription in English and in such other language as the ^1[State Government] directs:--"The`
  line `seal of the Registrar (or of the Sub-Registrar) of".`
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (37614)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Register-books and fire-proof boxes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for "Provincial Government".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338&sectionId=37614&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) The ^1[State Government] shall provide for the office`
  line `of every registering officer the books necessary for the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The books so provided shall contain the forms from time to time prescribed by the InspectorGeneral, with the sanction of the ^1[State Government], and the pages of such books shall be consecutively`
  line `numbered in print, and the number of pages in each book shall be certified on the title page by the officer`
  line `by whom such books are issued.`
  line
  line `(3) The ^1[State Government] shall supply the office of every Registrar with a fire-proof box, and shall`
  line `in each district make suitable provision for the safe custody of the records connected with the registration`
  line `of documents in such district.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_a:
  sectionId (37615)
  sectionNo 16A
  orderNo 17
  title `Keeping of books in computer floppies, diskettes, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 48 of 2001, s. 2 (w.e.f. 24-9-2001)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338&sectionId=37615&sectionno=16A&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338
obj_root_law_sections_16_a_content:
  string
  line `[16A. Keeping of books in computer floppies, diskettes, etc.-- (1) Notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in section 16, the books provided under sub-section (1) of that section may also be kept in`
  line `computer floppies or diskettes or in any other electronic form in the manner and subject to the safeguards`
  line `as may be prescribed by the Inspector-General with the sanction of the State Government.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act or in any other law for the time being in force, a`
  line `copy or extracts from the books kept under sub-section (1) given by the registering officer under his hand`
  line `and seal shall be deemed to be a copy given under section 57 for the purposes of sub-section (5) of that`
  line section.]
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (37616)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 18
  title `Documents of which registration is compulsory.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338&sectionId=37616&sectionno=17&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) The following documents shall`
  line `be registered, if the property to which they relate is situate in a district in which, and if they have been`
  line `executed on or after the date on which, Act No. XVI of 1864, or the Indian Registration Act, 1866, or the`
  line `Indian Registration Act, 1871, or the Indian Registration Act, 1877, or this Act came or comes into force,`
  line `namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) instruments of gift of immovable property;`
  line
  line `(b) other non-testamentary instruments which purport or operate to create, declare, assign, limit`
  line `or extinguish, whether in present or in future, any right, title or interest, whether vested or contingent,`
  line `of the value of one hundred rupees and upwards, to or in immovable property;`
  line
  line `(c) non-testamentary instruments which acknowledge the receipt or payment of any consideration`
  line `on account of the creation, declaration, assignment, limitation or extinction of any such right, title or`
  line `interest; and`
  line
  line `(d) leases of immovable property from year to year, or for any term exceeding one year, or`
  line `reserving a yearly rent;`
  line
  line `^1[(e) non-testamentary instruments transferring or assigning any decree or order of a Court or any`
  line `award when such decree or order or award purports or operates to create, declare, assign, limit or`
  line `extinguish, whether in present or in future, any right, title or interest, whether vested or contingent, of`
  line `the value of one hundred rupees and upwards, to or in immovable property:]`
  line
  line `Provided that the ^2[State Government] may, by order published in the ^3[Official Gazette], exempt`
  line `from the operation of this sub-section any lease executed in any district, or part of a district, the terms`
  line `granted by which do not exceed five years and the annual rents reserved by which do not exceed fifty`
  line rupees.
  line
  line `^4[(1A) The documents containing contracts to transfer for consideration, any immovable property for`
  line `the purpose of section 53A of the Transfer of Property Act, 1882 (4 of 1882) shall be registered if they`
  line `have been executed on or after the commencement of the Registration and Other Related laws`
  line `(Amendment) Act, 2001 (48 of 2001) and if such documents are not registered on or after such`
  line `commencement, then, they shall have no effect for the purposes of the said section 53A.]`
  line
  line `(2) Nothing in clauses (b) and (c) of sub-section (1) applies to--`
  line
  line `(i) any composition deed; or`
  line
  line `(ii) any instrument relating to shares in a joint stock Company, notwithstanding that the assets`
  line `of such Company consist in whole or in part of immovable property; or`
  line
  line `(iii) any debenture issued by any such Company and not creating, declaring, assigning,`
  line `limiting or extinguishing any right, title or interest, to or in immovable property except in so far`
  line `as it entitles the holder to the security afforded by a registered instrument whereby the Company`
  line `has mortgaged, conveyed or otherwise transferred the whole or part of its immovable property or`
  line `any interest therein to trustees upon trust for the benefit of the holders of such debentures; or`
  line
  line `(iv) any endorsement upon or transfer of any debenture issued by any such Company; or`
  line
  line `(v)`
  line `^5[any document other than the documents specified in sub-section (1A)] not itself`
  line `creating, declaring, assigning, limiting or extinguishing any right, title or interest of the value of`
  line `one hundred rupees and upwards to or in immovable property, but merely creating a right to`
  line `obtain another document which will, when executed, create, declare, assign, limit or extinguish`
  line `any such right, title or interest; or`
  line
  line `(vi) any decree or order of a Court ^6[except a decree or order expressed to be made on a`
  line `compromise and comprising immovable property other than that which is the subject-matter of`
  line `the suit or proceeding]; or`
  line
  line `(vii) any grant of immovable property by ^7[Government]; or`
  line
  line `(viii) any instrument of partition made by a Revenue-Officer; or`
  line
  line `(ix) any order granting a loan or instrument of collateral security granted under the Land`
  line `Improvement Act, 1871, or the Land Improvement Loans Act, 1883; or`
  line
  line `(x) any order granting a loan under the Agriculturists, Loans Act, 1884, or instrument for`
  line `securing the repayment of a loan made under that Act; or`
  line
  line `^8[(xa) any order made under the Charitable Endowments Act, 1890 (6 of 1890), vesting any`
  line `property in a Treasurer of Charitable Endowments or divesting any such Treasurer of any`
  line `property; or]`
  line
  line `(xi) any endorsement on a mortgage-deed acknowledging the payment of the whole or any`
  line `part of the mortgage-money, and any other receipt for payment of money due under a mortgage`
  line `when the receipt does not purport to extinguish the mortgage; or`
  line
  line `(xii) any certificate of sale granted to the purchaser of any property sold by public auction by`
  line `a Civil or Revenue-Officer.`
  line
  line `^9[Explanation.--A document purporting or operating to effect a contract for the sale of immovable`
  line `property shall not be deemed to require or ever to have required registration by reason only of the fact that`
  line `such document contains a recital of the payment of any earnest money or of the whole or any part of the`
  line `purchase money.]`
  line
  line `(3) Authorities to adopt a son, executed after the 1st day of January, 1872, and not conferred by a`
  line `will, shall also be registered.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENTS`
  line
  line Kerala
  line
  line `Amendment of section 17. --In section 17 of the Registration Act, 1908 (Central Act 16 of 1908)`
  line `(hereinafter referred to as the principal Act),--`
  line
  line `(i) in sub-section (1), after clause (e), the following clauses shall be inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `(f) Instruments purporting or operating to effect a contract for the sale of immovable property`
  line `of the value of one hundred rupees and upwards;`
  line
  line `(g) Power of attorney creating any power or right of management, administration, development,`
  line `transfer or any other transaction relating to immovable property of the value of one hundred rupees`
  line `and upwards other than those executed in favour of father, mother, wife, husband, son, adopted son,`
  line `daughter, adopted daughter, brother, sister, son-in-law or daughter-in-law of the executant.;`
  line
  line `(ii) in sub-section (2), the Explanation shall be omitted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Kerala Act 31 of 2013, s. 2]`
  line
  line Kerala
  line
  line `Amendment of section 17.---In sub-section (2) of section 17 of the Indian Registration Act, 1908`
  line `(Central Act 16 of 1908) (hereinafter referred to as the principal Act), clause (ix) and (x) shall be omitted.`
  line
  line `[Vide kerala Act 7 of 1968, s. 2]`
  line
  line Orissa
  line
  line `Amendment of section 17.-- In section 17 of the principal Act, in sub-section (1), after clause (e), the`
  line `following clauses shall be inserted before the proviso, namely:--`
  line
  line `(f) agreement to sell immovable property possession whereof has been or is handed over to the`
  line `purported purchaser;`
  line
  line `(g) power of-attorney relating to transfer of immovable property possession whereof has been or`
  line `is handed over to the purported attorney holder.`
  line
  line `[Vide Orissa Act 8 of 2002, s. 3]`
  line
  line Rajasthan
  line
  line `Amendment of section 17, Central Act XVI of 1908.--In sub-section (2) of section 17 of the Registration Act, 1908 (Central Act XVI of 1908), in its application to the State of Rajasthan, hereinafter referred to as the principal Act-`
  line
  line `(a) for the full-stop at the end of clause (xii) a comma and the word ,or shall be substituted; and`
  line
  line `(b) after clause (xii) as so amended, the following clause shall be added. namely :-`
  line
  line `"(xiii) any instrument referred to in sub-section (5) of section 89."`
  line
  line `[Vide Rajasthan Act 16 of 1976, s. 2]`
  line
  line `Amendment of section 17, Central Act 16 of 1908.--In section 17 of the Registration Act, 1908 (Central Act 16 of 1908), in its application to the State of Rajasthan, hereinafter referred to as the principal Act,-`
  line
  line `(a) in sub-section (1), after clause (e), and before the proviso, the following clauses shall be added, namely:-`
  line
  line `"(f) agreement to sell immovable property possession where of has been or is handed over to the purported purchaser;`
  line
  line `(g) irrevocable power of attorney relating to transfer of immovable property in any way;";and`
  line
  line `(b) in sub-section (2), the existing Explanation shall be omitted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Rajasthan Act 18 of 1989, s. 2]`
  line
  line Gujarat
  line
  line `Amendment of section 17 of XVI of 1908.--In the Registration Act, 1908, in its application to the State of Gujarat (hereinafter referred to as "the principal Act"), in section 17,--`
  line
  line `(i) in sub-section (1),--`
  line
  line `(a) for clause (f), the following clause shall be substituted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"(f) power of attorney intending to administer, manage and/or alienate immovable property in any manner, executed on or after the commencement of the Registration (Gujarat Amendment) Act, 2016(Guj.16 of 2016);":`
  line
  line `(b) after clause (j), the following clause shall be added, namely:--`
  line
  line `"(k) sale certificate issued by any competent officer or authority under any central Act or State Act for the time being in force.";`
  line
  line `(ii) in sub-section (2), clause (xii) shall be deleted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Gujarat Act 4 of 2020, s. 2]`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 21 of 1929, s. 10.`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for Provincial Government.`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for Local Official Gazette.`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by Act 48 of 2001, s. 3 (w.e.f. 24-9-2001).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 48 of 2001, s. 3, for any document (w.e.f. 24-9-2001).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by Act 21 of 1929, s. 10, for and any award.`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for Crown.`
  line
  line `8. Ins. by Act 39 of 1948, s. 2.`
  line
  line `9. Ins by Act 2 of 1927, s. 2.`
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (37617)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 19
  title `Documents of which registration is optional.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 33 of 1940, s. 2.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338&sectionId=37617&sectionno=18&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `Any of the following documents may be`
  line `registered under this Act, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) Instruments (other than instruments of gift and wills) which purport or operate to create,`
  line `declare, assign, limit or extinguish, whether in present or in future, any right, title or interest, whether`
  line `vested or contingent, of a value less then one hundred rupees, to or in immovable property;`
  line
  line `(b) instruments acknowledging the receipt or payment of any consideration on account of the`
  line `creation, declaration, assignment, limitation or extinction of any such right, title or interest;`
  line
  line `(c) leases of immovable property for any term not exceeding one year, and leases exempted under`
  line `section 17;`
  line
  line `^1[(cc) instruments transferring or assigning any decree or order of a Court or any award when`
  line `such decree or order or award purports or operates to create, declare, assign, limit or extinguish, whether in present or in future, any right, title or interest, whether vested or contingent, of a value less`
  line `than one hundred rupees, to or in immovable property;]`
  line
  line `(d) instruments (other than wills) which purport or operate to create, declare, assign, limit or`
  line `extinguish any right, title or interest to or in movable property;`
  line
  line `(e) wills; and`
  line
  line `(f) all other documents not required by section 17 to be registered.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line `Himachal Pradesh`
  line
  line `3. Insertion of new section 18A.- In the Indian Registration Act, 1908 (16 of 1908) (hereinafter`
  line `referred to as the principal Act), after section 18, the following section shall be inserted, namely;`
  line
  line `"18-A. Documents for registration to be accompanied by a true copy.- Notwithstanding`
  line `anything contained in this Act, the registering officer shall refuse to register any document presented`
  line `to him for registration unless such document is accompanied by a true copy thereof."`
  line
  line `[Vide Himachal Pradesh Act 2 of 1969, s. 3]`
  line
  line Tripura--
  line
  line `Insertion of new section 18A.--In the Registration Act, 1908 (hereinafter referred to as the principal`
  line `Act), after section 18, the following section shall be inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `18A. Document for Registration to be accompanied by a true copy.--(1)Notwithstanding`
  line `anything contained in the Act, the Registering Officer shall refuse to register any document presented to`
  line `him for registration unless such document is accompanied by a true copy thereof.`
  line
  line `(2) The true copy referred to in Sub-section (1) shall be neatly hand-written or printed or type-written`
  line `or lithographed or otherwise prepared in such manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `[Vide Tripura Act 7 of 1982, s. 2]`
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (37618)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 20
  title `Documents in language not understood by registering officer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338&sectionId=37618&sectionno=19&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `If any document duly`
  line `presented for registration be in a language which the registering officer does not understand, and which is`
  line `not commonly used in the district he shall refuse to register the documents, unless it be accompanied by a`
  line `true translation into a language commonly used in the district and also by a true copy.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line Karnataka
  line
  line `Insertion of new section 19A.--After section 19 of the Registration Act, 1908 (Central Act 16 of`
  line `1908) (hereinafter referred to as the principal Act), the following section shall be inserted namely:--`
  line
  line `"19A. Documents presented for registration to be accompanied by true copies thereof.--(1)`
  line `No document shall be accepted for registration unless it is accompanied by a true copy thereof.`
  line
  line `(2) The true copy referred to in sub-section (1) shall be neatly handwritten, printed, typewritten,`
  line `lithographed or otherwise prepared in accordance with such rules may be made in this matter."`
  line
  line `[Vide Karnataka Act 55 of 1976, s. 4]`
  line
  line Tripura--
  line
  line `Amendment of Section 19.---In section 19 of the principal Act, for the words "a true translation" the`
  line `words "two copies of the true translation" shall be substituted.`
  line `[Vide Tripura Act 7 of 1982, s. 3]`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line Kerala
  line
  line `Amendment of section 19.--In section 19 of the principal Act, the words "and also by a true copy"`
  line `shall be omitted.`
  line
  line `[Vide kerala Act 7 of 1968, s. 3]`
  line
  line `Insertion of new section 19A.---After section 19 of the principal Act, the following section shall be`
  line `inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"19A. Documents presented for registration to be accompanied by true copies thereof.--(1)`
  line `No documents shall be accepted for registration unless it is accompanied by a true copy thereof.`
  line
  line `(2) The true copy referred to in sub-section (1) shall be neatly handwritten, printed, typewritten,`
  line `lithographed or otherwise, prepared in accordance with such rules as may be made in this behalf."`
  line
  line `[Vide kerala Act 7 of 1968, s. 4]`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line `Himachal Pradesh`
  line
  line `4. Amendment of section 19.- In section 19 of the principal Act, for the words "a true`
  line `translation", the words "two copies of the true translation" shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Himachal Pradesh Act 2 of 1969, s. 4]`
  line
  line Orissa
  line
  line `Amendment of section 19.-- In the Registration Act, 1908 (16 of 1908) (hereinafter referred to as`
  line `the principal act), in section 19, the words " and also by a true copy" shall be omitted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Orissa Act 14 of 1989, s. 2]`
  line
  line `Insertion of new section 19-A.--In the principal Act, after section 19, the following section shall be`
  line `inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"19-A. Documents Presented for registration on to accompany true copies thereof.--(1) No`
  line `document shall be accepted for registration, unless it is accompanied by a true copy thereof.`
  line
  line `(2) The true copy referred to in sub-section (1) shall be legibly handwritten, printed, type-written,`
  line `lithographed, cyclostyled or otherwise prepared only on one side of the paper and in accordance with such`
  line `rules as may be made in this behalf by the State Government and shall contain a declaration in the`
  line `prescribed manner that the same is true copy of the document and its translation, if any.".`
  line
  line `[Vide Orissa Act 14 of 1989, s. 3]`
  line
  line Orissa
  line
  line `Amendment of section 19-A.--In Sub-section (2), for the words "otherwise prepared", the words`
  line `"otherwise legibly prepared" shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Orissa Act 8 of 2002, s. 4]`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (37619)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 21
  title `Documents containing interlineations, blanks, erasures or alterations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338&sectionId=37619&sectionno=20&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) The registering`
  line `officer may in his discretion refuse to accept for registration any document in which any interlineation,`
  line `blank, erasure or alteration appears, unless the persons executing the document attest with their signatures`
  line `or initials such interlineation, blank, erasure or alteration.`
  line
  line `(2) If the registering officer registers any such document, he shall, at the time of registering the same,`
  line `make a note in the register of such interlineation, blank, erasure or alteration.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (37620)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 22
  title `Description of property and maps or plans.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338&sectionId=37620&sectionno=21&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `(1) No non-testamentary document relating to`
  line `immovable property shall be accepted for registration unless it contains a description of such property`
  line `sufficient to identify the same.`
  line
  line `(2) Houses in towns shall be described as situate on the north or other side of the street or road (which`
  line `should be specified) to which they front, and by their existing and former occupancies, and by their`
  line `numbers if the houses in such street or road are numbered.`
  line
  line `(3) Other houses and lands shall be described by their name, if any, and as being the territorial`
  line `division in which they are situate, and by their superficial contents, the roads and other properties on to`
  line `which they abut, and their existing occupancies, and also, whenever it is practicable, by reference to a`
  line `Government map or survey.`
  line
  line `(4) No non-testamentary document containing a map or plan of any property comprised therein shall`
  line `be accepted for registration unless it is accompanied by a true copy of the map or plan, or, in case such`
  line `property is situate in several districts, by such number of true copies of the map or plan as are equal to the`
  line `number of such districts.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line Assam
  line
  line `Insertion of new Section 21A.-- In the principal Act, after the existing section 21, the following new`
  line `section 21A shall be inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"21A. No registration of non-testamentary instruments without no objection certificate.--`
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in any other provision of this Act, no non-testamentary instrument`
  line `relating to immovable property shall be accepted for registration, unless the Deputy Commissioner of the`
  line `concerned district issues a No Objection Certificate containing the description of such immovable`
  line `property to be transferred and also such other No objection Certificates, which are required to be issued`
  line `by the Deputy Commissioner or any other Authority under any law for the time being in force or under`
  line `any Executive Instruction, Order, etc., issued by the State Government from time-to-time:`
  line
  line `Provided that all such No Objection Certificates shall be issued within a period of thirty days from the`
  line `date of the receipt of application and in case No Objection Certificate is not issued within the stipulated`
  line `period of thirty days, a speaking order with reasons thereof shall be issued to the applicant within the said`
  line `stipulated period."`
  line
  line `[Vide Assam Act 29 of 2009, s. 2]`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (37621)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 23
  title `Description of houses and land by reference to Government maps or surveys.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for Provincial Government.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338&sectionId=37621&sectionno=22&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where it`
  line `is, in the opinion of the ^1[State Government], practicable to describe houses, not being houses in towns,`
  line `and lands by reference to a Government map or survey, the ^1[State Government] may, by rule made under`
  line `this Act, require that such houses and lands as aforesaid shall, for the purposes of section 21, be so`
  line described.
  line
  line `(2) Save as otherwise provided by any rule made under sub-section (1), failure to comply with the`
  line `provisions of section 21, sub-section (2) or sub-section (3), shall not disentitle a document to`
  line `be registered if the description of the property to which it relates is sufficient to identify that property.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line Karnataka
  line
  line `Insertion of new section 22A.--After section 22 of the principal Act, the following section shall be`
  line `inserted namely:--`
  line
  line `22A. Documents registration of which is opposed to public policy.--(1) The State`
  line `Government may, by notification, in the official Gazette, declare that the registration of any`
  line `document or class of documents is opposed to public policy.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, the registering officer shall refuse to register`
  line `any document to which a notification issued under sub-section (1) is applicable.`
  line
  line `[Vide Karnataka Act 55 of 1976, s. 5]`
  line
  line Orissa
  line
  line `Insertion of new section 22-A. --After section 22 of the principal Act, the following section shall be`
  line `inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `22-A. Document of section 17.--(1) The State Government may, by notification, declare that the`
  line `registration of any document or class of documents is opposed to public policy.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, the registering officer shall refuse to register a`
  line `document to which a notification issued under sub-section (1) is applicable.`
  line
  line `[Vide Orissa Act 8 of 2002, s. 5]`
  line
  line Orissa
  line
  line `Amendment of section 22-A.-- In the Registration Act, 1908 (16 of 1908), for section 22-A, the following section shall be substituted, namely:--`
  line
  line `22-A. Refusal to register certain documents.--(1) The registering officer shall refuse to register,--`
  line
  line `(a) any instrument relating to the transfer of immovable properties by way of sale, gift, mortgage,`
  line `exchange or lease,--`
  line
  line `(i) belonging to the State Government , or the Local Authority;`
  line
  line `(ii) belonging to any religious institution to which the Odisha Hindu Religious Endowment`
  line `Act, 1951 (Odisha Act 2 of 1952) is applicable.`
  line
  line `(iii) belonging to or recorded in the name of Lord Jagannath, Puri;`
  line
  line `(iv) donated for Bhoodan Yagna and vested in the Odisha Bhoodan Yagna Samiti established`
  line `under section 3 of the Odisha Bhoodan and Gramdan Act, 1970 (Odisha Act 2 of 1971);`
  line
  line `(v) belonging to Wakfs which are under the supervision of Odisha Wakf Board established`
  line `under the Wakf Act, 1995 (43 of 1995); unless a sanction in this regard, issued by the competent`
  line `authority as provided under the relevant Act or in absence of any such authority, and authority so`
  line `authorized by the State Government for this purpose, is produced before the registering officer;`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purpose of this section Local Authority means any Municipal Corporation,`
  line `Municipality, Notified Area Council, Zilla Parisad, Grama Panchayat, Urban Development Authority`
  line `and Planning Authority or any Local Self Government constituted under any law for the time being in`
  line force.
  line
  line `(b)The instrument relating to cancellation of sale deeds without the consent of the person`
  line `claiming under the said sale deed; and`
  line
  line `(c) Any instrument relating to transfer of immovable property, the alienation or transfer of which`
  line `is prohibited under any State or the Central Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, the registering officer shall not register any`
  line `document presented to him for registration unless the transferor produce the record of rights for the`
  line `satisfaction of the registering officer that such transferor has right, title and interest over the property so`
  line transferred.
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purpose of this sub-section 'record-of-rights' means the record of rights as`
  line `defined under the Odisha Survey and Settlement Act, 1958 (Odisha Act 3 of 1959).`
  line
  line `[Vide Orissa Act 1 of 2014, s. 2]`
  line
  line Rajasthan
  line
  line `Insertion of section 22-A in Central Act XVI of 1908.— After section 22 of the principal Act, the`
  line `following section shall be inserted, namely:-`
  line
  line `22-A. Documents registration of which is opposed to public policy.-(1) The State Government`
  line `may, by notification in the Official Gazette, declare that the registration of any document or class of`
  line `documents is opposed to public policy.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, the registering officer shall refuse to register a`
  line `document to which a notification issued under sub-section (1) is applicable.`
  line
  line `[Vide Rajasthan Act 16 of 1976, s. 3]`
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (37622)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 24
  title `Time for presenting documents.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338&sectionId=37622&sectionno=23&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions contained in sections 24, 25 and 26,`
  line `no document other than a will shall be accepted for registration unless presented for that purpose to the`
  line `proper officer within four months from the date of its execution:`
  line
  line `Provided that a copy a of a decree or order may be presented within four months from the day on`
  line `which the decree or order was made, or, where it is appealable, within four months from the day on which`
  line `it becomes final.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23_a:
  sectionId (37623)
  sectionNo 23A
  orderNo 25
  title `Re-registration of certain documents.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 15 of 1917, s. 2.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338&sectionId=37623&sectionno=23A&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338
obj_root_law_sections_23_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[23A. Re-registration of certain documents.--Notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained`
  line `in this Act, if in any case a document requiring registration has been accepted for registration by a`
  line `Registrar or Sub-Registrar from a person not duly empowered to present the same, and has been`
  line `registered, any person claiming under such document may, within four months form his first becoming`
  line `aware that the registration of such document is invalid, present such document or cause the same to be`
  line `presented, in accordance with the provisions of Part VI for re-registration in the office of the Registrar of`
  line `the district in which the document was originally registered; and upon the Registrar being satisfied that`
  line `the document was so accepted for registration from a person not duly empowered to present the same, he`
  line `shall proceed to the re-registration of the document as if it has not been previously registered, and as if`
  line `such presentation for re-registration was a presentation for registration made within the time allowed`
  line `therefore under Part IV, and all the provisions of this Act, as to registration of documents, shall apply to`
  line `such re-registration; and such document, if duly re-registered in accordance with the provisions of this`
  line `section, shall be deemed to have been duly registered for all purposes from the date of its original`
  line `registration:`
  line
  line `Provided that, within three months from the twelfth day of September, 1917, any person claiming`
  line `under a document to which this section applies may present the same or cause the same to be presented`
  line `for re-registration in accordance with this section, whatever may have been the time when he first became`
  line `aware that the registration of the document was invalid.]`
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (37624)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 26
  title `Documents executed by several persons at different times.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338&sectionId=37624&sectionno=24&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `Where there are several persons`
  line `executing a document at different times, such document may be presented for registration and`
  line `re-registration within four months from the date of each execution.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (37625)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 27
  title `Provision where delay in presentation is unavoidable.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 3 of 1951, s. 3 and the Schedule, for the State.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338&sectionId=37625&sectionno=25&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `(1) If, owing to urgent necessity or`
  line `unavoidable accident, any document executed, or copy of a decree or order made, in ^1[India] is not`
  line `presented for registration till after the expiration of the time hereinbefore prescribed in that behalf, the`
  line `Registrar, in cases where the delay in presentation does not exceed four months, may direct that, on`
  line `payment of a fine not exceeding ten times the amount of the proper registration-fee, such document shall`
  line `be accepted for registration.`
  line
  line `(2) Any application for such direction may be lodged with a Sub-Registrar, who shall forthwith`
  line `forward it to the Registrar to whom he is subordinate.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line Rajasthan
  line
  line `Amendment of section 25, Central Act 16 of 1908.- In section 25 of the principal Act,—`
  line
  line `(a) in sub-section (1), for the word Registrar the words Registering Officer, for the words`
  line `direct that, the words register the document and for the expression ,such document shall be`
  line `accepted for registration, the words on such document shall be substituted; and`
  line
  line `(b) sub-section (2) shall be omitted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Rajasthan Act 18 of 1989, s. 3]`
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (37626)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 28
  title `Documents executed out of India.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 3 of 1951, s. 3 and the Schedule, for "the State".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338&sectionId=37626&sectionno=26&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `When a document purporting to have been executed by all`
  line `or any of the parties out of ^1[India] is not presented for registration till after the expiration of the time`
  line `hereinbefore prescribed in that behalf, the registering officer, if satisfied--`
  line
  line `(a) that the instrument was so executed, and`
  line
  line `(b) that it has been presented for registration within four months after its arrival in ^1[India],`
  line
  line `may, on payment of the proper registration-fee accept such document for registration.`
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (37627)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 29
  title `Wills may be presented or deposited at any time.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338&sectionId=37627&sectionno=27&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `A will may at any time be presented for`
  line `registration or deposited in manner hereinafter provided.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (37628)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 30
  title `Place for registering documents relating to land.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338&sectionId=37628&sectionno=28&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `Save as in this Part otherwise provided,`
  line `every document mentioned in section 17, sub-section (1), clauses (a), (b), (c)`
  line ^1
  line `[, (d) and (e), section 17,`
  line `sub-section (2), insofar as such document affects immovable property,]and section 18, clauses (a), (b)`
  line `^2[(c) and (cc),] shall be presented for registration in the office of a Sub-Registrar within whose`
  line `sub-district the whole or some portion of the property to which such document relates is situate.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line Orissa
  line
  line `Amendment of section 28.--In section 28 of the principal Act,--`
  line
  line `(i) for the word, brackets and letter and (e) , the commas, brackets, letters and word, (e), (f)`
  line `and (g) shall be substituted; and`
  line
  line `(ii) the words or some portion shall be omitted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Orissa Act 8 of 2002, s. 6]`
  line
  line Rajasthan
  line
  line `Amendment of section 30, Central Act 16 of 1908.-In section 30 of the principal Act, the`
  line `brackets and figure (l) and sub-section (2) shall be omitted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Rajasthan Act 18 of 1989, s. 4]`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 33 of 1940, s. 3, for and (d).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 33 of 1940, s. 3, for and (c)`
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (37629)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 31
  title `Place for registering other documents.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338&sectionId=37629&sectionno=29&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every document ^1[not being a document referred to`
  line `in section 28 or a copy of a decree or order], may be presented for registration either in the office of the`
  line `Sub-Registrar in whose sub-district the document was executed, or in the office of any other`
  line `Sub-Registrar under the ^2[State Government at which all the persons executing and claiming under the`
  line `document desire the same to be registered.`
  line
  line `(2) A copy of a decree or order may be presented for registration in the office of the Sub-Registrar in`
  line `whose sub-district the original decree or order was made, or, where the decree or order does not affect`
  line `immovable property, in the office of any the Sub-Registrar under the ^1[State Government] at which all the`
  line `persons claiming under the decree or order desire the copy to be registered.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 32 of 1940, s. 3 and the first Schedule, for certain words.`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for "Provincial Government".`
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (37630)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 32
  title `Registration by Registrars in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes `1. Sub-section (2) omitted by Act 48 of 2001, s. 4 (w.e.f. 24-9-2001).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338&sectionId=37630&sectionno=30&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any Registrar may in his discretion receive`
  line `and register any document which might be registered by any Sub-Registrar subordinate to him.`
  line
  line `^1* * * * *`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line Karnataka
  line
  line `Amendment of section 30.--In Section 30 of the Registration Act, 1908 (Central Amendment 16 of`
  line `1908) (hereinafter referred to as the principal Act), the brackets and figure (1) and 'sub-section (2)' shall`
  line `be omitted.]`
  line
  line `[Vide Karnataka Act 24 of 1989, s. 2]`
  line
  line Orissa
  line
  line `Amendment of section 30.--In the Registration Act, 1908 (16 of 1908) (hereinafter referred to as the`
  line `principal Act), in section 30, sub-section (2) shall be omitted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Orissa Act 19 of 1991, s. 2]`
  line
  line Haryana
  line
  line `Amendment of section 30 of Central Act 16 of 1908.--Sub-section (2) of section 30 of the Registration`
  line `Act, 1908 (hereinafter referred to as the principal Act), shall be omitted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Haryana Act 4 of 1997, s. 2]`
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (37631)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 33
  title `Registration or acceptance for deposit at private residence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338&sectionId=37631&sectionno=31&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `In ordinary cases the registration`
  line `or deposit of documents under this Act shall be made only at the office of the officer authorised to accept`
  line `the same for registration or deposit:`
  line
  line `Provided that such officer may on special cause being shown attend at the residence of any person`
  line `desiring to present a document for registration or to deposit a will, and accept for registration or deposit`
  line `such document or will.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (37632)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 34
  title `Persons to present documents for registration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 39 of 1948, s. 3, for section 31 and section 89.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338&sectionId=37632&sectionno=32&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `Except in the cases mentioned in ^1[sections`
  line `31, 88 and 89], every document to be registered under this Act, whether such registration be compulsory`
  line `or optional, shall be presented at the proper registration-office,--`
  line
  line `(a) by some person executing or claiming under the same, or, in the case of a copy of a decree or`
  line `order, claiming under the decree or order, or`
  line
  line `(b) by the representive or assign of such a person, or`
  line
  line `(c) by the agent of such a person, representative or assign, duly authorised by power-of attorney executed and authenticated in manner hereinafter mentioned.`
  line
  line Gujarat
  line
  line `Amendment of section 32 of XVI of 1908.--In the principal Act, in section 32, the following Explanation shall be added at the end, namely:--`
  line
  line `“Explanation.--For the purpose of this section the term “document” shall include the document presented by an electronic means.”`
  line
  line `[Vide Gujarat Act 4 of 2020, s. 3]`
obj_root_law_sections_32_a:
  sectionId (37633)
  sectionNo 32A
  orderNo 35
  title `Compulsory affixing of photograph, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 48 of 2001, s. 5 (w.e.f. 24-9-2001).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338&sectionId=37633&sectionno=32A&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338
obj_root_law_sections_32_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[32A. Compulsory affixing of photograph, etc.--Every person presenting any document at the`
  line `proper registration office under section 32 shall affix his passport size photograph and fingerprints to the`
  line `document:`
  line
  line `Provided that where such document relates to the transfer of ownership of immovable property, the`
  line `passport size photograph and fingerprints of each buyer and seller of such property mentioned in the`
  line `document shall also be affixed to the document.]`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line Uttarakhand
  line
  line `Amendment of section 32-A.--In section 32-A of the Principal act,--`
  line `(1) in sub-section (1)-`
  line
  line `(i) the words, "in such areas as may be notified by the State Government", shall be omitted;`
  line
  line `(ii) the word photostat wherever occurring including heading, shall be omitted;`
  line
  line `(2) in sub-section (2)-`
  line
  line `(i) for the words "photostat copy" the words "true copy" shall be substituted;`
  line
  line `(ii) for clauses (b) and (c), the following clause shall be inserted, namely:-`
  line
  line `"(b) be compared and verified by such official as may be directed by the Registering Officer."`
  line
  line `(3) Sub-section (3) shall be omitted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Uttarakhand Act 24 of 2014, s.7]`
  line
  line `Repealed at section 32-B.--Section 32-B of the Principal Act shall be repealed.`
  line
  line `[Vide Uttarkhand Act 24 of 2014, s. 8]`
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (37693)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 36
  title `Power-of-attorney recognisable for purposes of section 32.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338&sectionId=37693&sectionno=33&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `(1) For the purposes of section`
  line `32, the following powers-of-attorney shall alone be recognized, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) if the principal at the time of executing the power-of-attorney resides in any part of ^1`
  line `[India] in`
  line `which this Act is for the time being in force, a power-of-attorney executed before and authenticated`
  line `by the Registrar or Sub-Registrar within whose district or sub-district the principal resides;`
  line
  line `(b) if the principal at the time aforesaid ^2[resides in any part of India in which this Act is not in`
  line `force, a power-of-attorney executed before and authenticated by any Magistrate;`
  line
  line `(c) if the principal at the time aforesaid does not reside in ^1India, a power-of-attorney executed`
  line `before and authenticated by a Notary Public, or any Court, Judge, Magistrate, ^3[Indian] Consul or`
  line `Vice-Consul, or representative ^4***of the Central Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that the following persons shall not be required to attend at any registration-office or Court`
  line `for the purpose of executing any such power-of-attorney as is mentioned in clauses (a) and (b) of this`
  line `section, namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) persons who by reason of bodily infirmity are unable without risk or serious inconvenience so`
  line `to attend;`
  line
  line `(ii) persons who are in jail under civil or criminal process; and`
  line
  line `(iii) persons exempt by law from personal appearance in court.`
  line
  line `^5[Explanation.In this sub-section India means India, as defined in clause (28) of section 3 of the`
  line `General Clauses Act, 1897 (10 of 1897).]`
  line
  line `(2) In the case of every such person the Registrar or Sub-Registrar or Magistrate, as the case may be,`
  line `if satisfied that the power-of-attorney has been voluntarily executed by the person purporting to be the`
  line `principal, may attest the same without requiring his personal attendance at the office or Court aforesaid.`
  line
  line `(3) To obtain evidence as to the voluntary nature of the execution, the Registrar or Sub-Registrar or`
  line `Magistrate may either himself go to the house of the person purporting to be the principal, or to the jail in`
  line `which he is confined, and examine him, or issue a commission for his examination.`
  line
  line `(4) Any power-of-attorney mentioned in this section may be proved by the production of it without`
  line `further proof when it purports on the face of it to have been executed before and authenticated by the`
  line `person or Court hereinbefore mentioned in that behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 3 of 1951, s. 3 and the Schedule, for "the State".`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 3 of 1951, s. 3, and the Schedule, for resides in any other part of the States.`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for "British".`
  line
  line `4. The words of His Majesty or omitted, ibid.`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by Act 3 of 1951, s. 3 and the Schedule.`
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (37696)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 37
  title `Enquiry before registration by registering officer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338&sectionId=37696&sectionno=34&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions contained in`
  line `this Part and in sections 41, 43, 45, 69, 75, 77, 88 and 89, no document shall be registered under this Act,`
  line `unless the persons executing such document, or their representatives, assigns or agents authorised as`
  line `aforesaid, appear before the registering officer within the time allowed for presentation under sections 23,`
  line `24, 25 and 26:c`
  line `Provided that, if owing to urgent necessity or unavoidable accident all such persons do not so appear,`
  line `the Registrar, in cases where the delay in appearing does not exceed four months, may direct that on`
  line `payment of a fine not exceeding ten times the amount of the proper registration fee, in addition to the fine,`
  line `if any, payable under section 25, the document may be registered.`
  line
  line `(2) Appearances under sub-section (1) may be simultaneous or at different times.`
  line
  line `(3) The registering officer shall thereupon--`
  line
  line `(a) enquire whether or not such document was executed by the persons by whom it purports to`
  line `have been executed;`
  line
  line `(b) satisfy himself as to the identity of the persons appearing before him and alleging that they`
  line `have executed the document; and (c) in the case of any person appearing as a representative, assign or agent, satisfy himself of the`
  line `right of such person so to appear.`
  line
  line `(4) Any application for a direction under the proviso to sub-section (1) may be lodged with a SubRegistrar, who shall forthwith forward it to the Registrar to whom he is subordinate.`
  line
  line `(5) Nothing in this section applies to copies of decrees or orders.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENEDMENT`
  line
  line Gujarat
  line
  line `Amendment of section 34 of XVI of 1908.--In the principal Act, in section 34,--`
  line `(i) after sub-section (1), the following sub-section shall be inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `“(1A) The registering officer may refuse to accept the non-testamentary documents relating to immovable property mentioned in sub-section (1) of section 17, if they are not accompanied by the—`
  line
  line `(a) proofs of identify of executing and claiming parties and witnesses;`
  line
  line `(b) proofs of authorization when the executant or claimant thereunder is representative or agent authorized by the person or entity whose document is so be registered;`
  line
  line `(c) sign or thumb impression/finger print (if the person is unable to sign) of one person from both executing and claiming parties, affixed on each and every page of the deeds submitted for registration;`
  line
  line `(d) proof that the principal is alive, in cases where the document is executed by the power of attorney holder on behalf of the principal.”;`
  line
  line `(ii) the following Explanation shall be added at the end, namely:-`
  line
  line `“Explanation.---For the purpose of this section the term “document” shall include the document presented by an electronic means.”.`
  line
  line `[Vide Gujarat Act 4 of 2020, s. 4]`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (37635)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 38
  title `Procedure on admission and denial of execution respectively.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338&sectionId=37635&sectionno=35&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `(1) (a) If all the persons`
  line `executing the document appear personally before the registering officer and are personally known to him,`
  line `or if he be otherwise satisfied that they are the person they represent themselves to be, and if they all`
  line `admit the execution of the document, or`
  line
  line `(b) if in the case of any person appearing by a representative, assign or agent, such representative,`
  line `assign or agent admits the execution, or`
  line
  line `(c) if the person executing the document is dead, and his representative or assign appears before`
  line `the registering officer and admits the execution,`
  line
  line `the registering officer shall register the document as directed in sections 58 to 61 inclusive.`
  line
  line `(2) The registering officer may, in order to satisfy himself that the persons appearing before him are`
  line `the persons they represent themselves to be, or for any other purpose contemplated by this Act, examine`
  line `any one present in his office.`
  line
  line `(3) (a) If any person by whom the document purports to be executed denies its execution, or`
  line
  line `(b) if any such person appears to the registering officer to be a minor, an idiot or a lunatic, or`
  line
  line `(c) if any person by whom the document purports to be executed is dead, and his representative or`
  line `assign denies its execution,`
  line
  line `the registering officer shall refuse to register the document as to the person so denying, appearing`
  line `or dead:`
  line
  line `Provided that, where such officer is a Registrar, he shall follow the procedure prescribed in Part XII:`
  line
  line `^1[Provided further that the ^2`
  line `State Government may, by notification in the ^3`
  line `Official Gazette, declare that any Sub-Registrar named in the notification shall, in respect of documents the execution of which is denied, be deemed to be a Registrar for the purposes of this sub-section and of Part XII.]`
  line
  line `STATE AMENEDMENT`
  line
  line Gujarat
  line
  line `Amendment of section 35 of XVI of 1908.—(l) In the principal Act, in section 35,the following Explanation shall be added at the end, namely:-`
  line
  line `“Explanation.- For the purpose of this section the term “document” shall include the document presented by an electronic means.”.`
  line
  line `[Vide Gujarat Act 4 of 2020, s. 5]`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 13 of 1926, s. 2.`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for Provincial Government.`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by the A.O. 1939, for Local Official Gazette.`
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (37636)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 39
  title `Procedure where appearance of executant or witness is desired.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for "Provincial Government".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338&sectionId=37636&sectionno=36&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `If any person presenting`
  line `any document for registration or claiming under any document, which is capable of being so presented,`
  line `desires the appearance of any person whose presence or testimony is necessary for the registration of such`
  line `document, the registering officer may, in his discretion, call upon such Officer or Court as the ^1[State`
  line `Government] directs in this behalf to issue a summons requiring him to appear at the registration office,`
  line `either in person or by duly authorised agent, as in the summons may be mentioned, and at a time named`
  line therein.
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (37637)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 40
  title `Officer or Court to issue and cause service of summons.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338&sectionId=37637&sectionno=37&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `The officer or Court, upon receipt of`
  line `the peon's fee payable in such cases, shall issue the summons accordingly, and cause it to be served upon`
  line `the person whose appearance is so required.`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (37638)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 41
  title `Persons exempt from appearance at registration-office.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338&sectionId=37638&sectionno=38&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `(1) (a) A person who by reason of`
  line `bodily infirmity is unable without risk or serious inconvenience to appear at the registration-office, or`
  line
  line `(b) a person in jail under civil or criminal process, or`
  line
  line `(c) person exempt by law from personal appearance in Court, and who would but for the`
  line `provisions next hereinafter contained be required to appear in person at the registration-office, shall`
  line `not be required so to appear.`
  line
  line `(2) In the case of every such person the registering officer shall either himself go to the house of such`
  line `person, or to the jail in which he is confined, and examine him or issue a commission for his examination.`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (37639)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 42
  title `Law as to summonses, commissions and witnesses.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338&sectionId=37639&sectionno=39&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `The law in force for the time being as to`
  line `summonses, commissions and compelling the attendance of witnesses, and for their remuneration in suits`
  line `before Civil Courts, shall, save as aforesaid and mutatis mutandis, apply to any summons or commission`
  line `issued and any person summoned to appear under the provisions of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (37640)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 43
  title `Persons entitled to present wills and authorities to adopt.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338&sectionId=37640&sectionno=40&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `(1) The testator, or after his death`
  line `any person claiming as executor or otherwise under a will, may present it to any Registrar or`
  line `Sub-Registrar for registration.`
  line
  line `(2) The donor, or after his death the done, of any authority to adopt, or the adoptive son, may present`
  line `it to any Registrar or Sub-Registrar for registration.`
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (37641)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 44
  title `Registration of wills and authorities to adopt.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338&sectionId=37641&sectionno=41&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `(1) A will or an authority to adopt, presented`
  line `for registration by the testator or donor, may be registered in the same manner as any other document.`
  line
  line `(2) A will or authority to adopt presented for registration by any other person entitled to present it`
  line `shall be registered if the registering officer is satisfied--`
  line
  line `(a) that the will or authority was executed by the testator or donor, as the case may be;`
  line
  line `(b) that the testator or donor is dead; and`
  line
  line `(c) that the person presenting the will or authority is, under section 40, entitled to present the`
  line same.
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (37642)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 45
  title `Deposit of wills.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338&sectionId=37642&sectionno=42&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `Any testator may, either personally or by duly authorised agent, deposit with`
  line `any Registrar his will in a sealed cover super scribed with the name of the testator and that of his agent (if`
  line `any) and with a statement of the nature of the document.`
obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (37643)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 46
  title `Procedure on deposit of wills.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338&sectionId=37643&sectionno=43&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `(1) On receiving such cover, the Registrar, if satisfied that the`
  line `person presenting the same for deposit is the testator or his agent, shall transcribe in his Register-book`
  line `No. 5 the superscription aforesaid, and shall note in the same book and on the said cover the year, month,`
  line `day and hour of such presentation and receipt, and the names of any persons who may testify to the`
  line `identity of the testator or his agent, and any legible inscription which may be on the seal of the cover.`
  line
  line `(2) The Registrar shall then place and retain the sealed cover in his fire-proof box.`
obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (37644)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 47
  title `Withdrawal of sealed cover deposited under section 42.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338&sectionId=37644&sectionno=44&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `If the testator who has deposited`
  line `such cover wishes to withdraw it, he may apply, either personally or by duly authorised agent, to the`
  line `Registrar who holds it in deposit, and such Registrar, if satisfied that the applicant is actually the testator`
  line `or his agent, shall deliver the cover accordingly.`
obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (37645)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 48
  title `Proceedings on death of depositor.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338&sectionId=37645&sectionno=45&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `(1) If, on the death of a testator who has deposited a sealed`
  line `cover under section 42, application be made to the Registrar who holds it in deposit to open the same, and`
  line `if the Registrar is satisfied that the testator is dead, he shall, in the applicant's presence, open the cover,`
  line `and, at the applicant's expense, cause the contents thereof to be copied into his Book No. 3.`
  line
  line `(2) When such copy has been made, the Registrar shall re-deposit the original will.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENTS`
  line
  line Karnataka
  line
  line `Amendment of section 45.--in section 45 of the principal Act,--`
  line
  line `(a) in sub-section (1), for the words, letters and figure cause the contents thereof to be copied`
  line `into his Book No. 3", the words, letters and figure "cause a true copy of the contents thereof to be`
  line `made and filled in his Book No. 3" shall be substituted;`
  line
  line `(b) in sub-section (2) for the words "copy has been made", the words "true copy has been filed"`
  line `shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Karnataka Act 55 of 1976, s. 6]`
  line
  line Tripura--
  line
  line `Amendment of Section 45.--In section 45 of the principal Act,--`
  line
  line `(a) In sub-section (1), for the words and figure "cause the contents thereof to be copied into his Book`
  line `No. 3", the words and figure "cause a true copy of the contents thereof to be made and pasted in`
  line `his Book No. 3" shall be substituted; and`
  line
  line `(b) In sub-section (2), for the words "copy has been made", the words "true copy has been pasted"`
  line `shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Tripura Act 7 of 1982, s. 4]`
  line
  line Kerala
  line
  line `Amendment of section 45.--In section 45 of the principal Act, --`
  line
  line `(a) in sub-section (1), for the words, letters and figure "cause the contents thereof to be copied`
  line `into his Book No. 3, the words, letters and figures "cause a true copy of the contents thereof to be`
  line `made and filed in his Book No. 3" shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `(b) in sub-section (2), for the words "copy has been made", the words true copy has been filed"`
  line `shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `[Vide kerala Act 7 of 1968, s. 5]`
  line
  line Orissa
  line
  line `Amendment of section 45.--In the principal Act, in section 45,--`
  line
  line `(a) in sub-section (1), for the words letters and figure "cause the contents thereof to be copied into`
  line `his Book No. 3", the words, letters and figure "cause a true copy of the contents there of to be made`
  line `and filed in his Book No.3" shall be substituted; and`
  line
  line `(b) in sub-section (2), for the words, "copy has been made", the words "true copy has been filed"`
  line `shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Orissa Act 14 of 1989, s. 4]`
obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_46:
  sectionId (37646)
  sectionNo (46)
  orderNo 49
  title `Saving of certain enactments and powers of Courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_46_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338&sectionId=37646&sectionno=46&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338
obj_root_law_sections_46_content:
  string
  line `(1) Nothing hereinbefore contained shall`
  line `affect the provisions of section 259 of the Indian Succession Act, 1865, or of section 81 of the Probate`
  line `and Administration Act, 1881, or the power of any Court by order to compel the production of any will.`
  line
  line `(2) When any such order is made, the Registrar shall, unless the will has been already copied under`
  line `section 45, open the cover and cause the will to be copied into his Book No. 3 and make a note on such`
  line `copy that the original has been removed into Court in pursuance of the order aforesaid.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENTS`
  line
  line Karnataka
  line
  line `Amendment of section 46.--In sub-section (2) of section 46 of the principal Act--`
  line
  line `(a) for the words "unless the will has been already copied", the words "unless a true copy of the`
  line `will has already been filled" shall be substituted;`
  line
  line `(b) for the words, letters and figure "cause the will to be copied into his Book No.3", the words,`
  line `letters and figure "cause a true copy of the will to be made and filed in his Book No. 3" shall be`
  line substituted.
  line
  line `[Vide Karnataka Act 55 of 1976, s. 7]`
  line
  line Tripura
  line
  line `Amendment of Section 46.--In section (2) of section 46 of the principal Act,--`
  line
  line `(a) For the words "unless the will has been already copied”, the words "unless a true copy of the will`
  line `has been already pasted" shall be substituted; and`
  line
  line `(b) For the words and figure "cause the will to be copied into his book No.3", the words and figure`
  line `"cause a true copy of the will to be made and pasted in his Book No. 3" shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Tripura Act 7 of 1982, s. 5]`
  line
  line Kerala
  line
  line `Amendment of section 46.--In sub-section (2) of section 46 of the principal Act,--`
  line
  line `(a) for the words "unless the will has been already copied", the words "unless a true copy of the`
  line `will has already been filed" shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `(b) for the words, letters and figure "cause the will to be copied into his Book No. 3", the words,`
  line `letters and figure "cause a true copy of the will to be made and filed in his Book No. 3" shall be`
  line substituted.
  line
  line `[Vide kerala Act 7 of 1968, s. 6]`
  line
  line Orissa
  line
  line `Amendment of section 46.-- In the principal Act, in sub-section (2) of section 46,--`
  line
  line `(a) for the words "unless the will has been already copied", the words " unless a true copy of the`
  line `will has already been filed" shall be substituted; and`
  line
  line `(b) for the words, letters and figure "cause the will to be copied in his Book No.3", the words,`
  line `letters and figure "cause a true copy of the will to be made and filed in his Book No.3" shall be`
  line substituted.
  line
  line `[Vide Orissa Act 14 of 1989, s. 5]`
obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_47:
  sectionId (37647)
  sectionNo (47)
  orderNo 50
  title `Time from which registered document operates.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_47_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338&sectionId=37647&sectionno=47&orderno=50&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338
obj_root_law_sections_47_content:
  string
  line `A registered document shall operate from`
  line `the time which it would have commenced to operate if no registration thereof had been required or made,`
  line `and not from the time of its registration.`
obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_48:
  sectionId (37648)
  sectionNo (48)
  orderNo 51
  title `Registered documents relating to property when to take effect against oral agreements.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_48_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 21 of 1929, s. 10.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338&sectionId=37648&sectionno=48&orderno=51&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338
obj_root_law_sections_48_content:
  string
  line `All non-testamentary documents duly registered under this Act, and relating to any`
  line `property, whether movable or immovable, shall take effect against any order agreement or declaration`
  line `relating to such property, unless where the agreement or declaration has been accompanied or followed`
  line `by delivery of possession ^1[and the same constitutes a valid transfer under any law for the time being in`
  line `force:`
  line
  line `Provided that a mortgage as defined in section 58 of the Transfer of Property Act, 1882 (4 of 1882),`
  line `shall take effect against any mortgage-deed subsequently executed and registered which relates to the`
  line `same property.]`
obj_root_law_sections_49:
  sectionId (37649)
  sectionNo (49)
  orderNo 52
  title `Effect of non-registration of documents required to be registered.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_49_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338&sectionId=37649&sectionno=49&orderno=52&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338
obj_root_law_sections_49_content:
  string
  line `No document required by`
  line `section 17 ^1[or by any provision of the Transfer of Property Act, 1882 (4 of 1882),] to be registered`
  line shall--
  line
  line `(a) affect any immovable property comprised therein, or`
  line
  line `(b) confer any power to adopt, or`
  line
  line `(c) be received as evidence of any transaction affecting such property or conferring such power,`
  line `unless it has been registered:`
  line
  line `^1[Provided that an unregistered document affecting immovable property and required by this Act or`
  line `the Transfer of Property Act, 1882 (4 of 1882), to be registered may be received as evidence of a contract`
  line `in a suit for specific performance under Chapter II of the Specific Relief Act, 1877 (3 of 1877) ^2[`
  line ,^3***
  line or
  line `as evidence of any collateral transaction not required to be effected by registered instrument.]`
obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 21 of 1929, s. 10.`
  line
  line `2. See now the Specific Relief Act, 1963 (47 of 1963).`
  line
  line `3. The words, figures and letter "or as evidence of part performance of a contract for the purposes of section 53A of the Transfer`
  line `of Property Act, 1882 (4 of 1882)" omitted by Act 48 of 2001, s. 6 (w.e.f. 24-9-2001).`
obj_root_law_sections_50:
  sectionId (37650)
  sectionNo (50)
  orderNo 53
  title `Certain registered documents relating to land to take effect against unregistered documents.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_50_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338&sectionId=37650&sectionno=50&orderno=53&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338
obj_root_law_sections_50_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every document of the kinds mentioned in clauses (a), (b), (c) and (d) of section 17,`
  line `sub-section (1), and clauses (a) and (b) of section 18, shall, if duly registered, take effect as regards the`
  line `property comprised therein, against every unregistered document relating to the same property, and not`
  line `being a decree or order, whether such unregistered document be of the same nature as the registered`
  line `document or not.`
  line
  line `(2) Nothing in sub-section (1) applies to leases exempted under the proviso to sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 17 or to any document mentioned in sub-section (2) of the same section, or to any registered`
  line `document which had not priority under the law in force at the commencement of this Act.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--In cases, where Act No. 16 of 1864 or the Indian Registration Act, 1866 (20 of 1866),`
  line `was in force in the place and at the time in and at which such unregistered document was executed,`
  line `"unregistered" means not registered according to such Act, and, where the document is executed after the first day of July, 1871, not registered under the Indian Registration Act, 1871 (8 of 1871), or the Indian`
  line `Registration Act, 1877 (3 of 1877), or this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_51:
  sectionId (37651)
  sectionNo (51)
  orderNo 54
  title `Register-books to be kept in the several offices.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_51_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338&sectionId=37651&sectionno=51&orderno=54&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338
obj_root_law_sections_51_content:
  string
  line `(1) The following books shall be kept in the`
  line `several offices hereinafter named, namely:--`
  line
  line `A--In all registration offices.--`
  line
  line `Book 1, "Register of non-testamentary documents relating to immovable property".`
  line
  line `Book 2, "Record of reasons for refusal to register".`
  line
  line `Book 3, "Register of wills and authorities to adopt", and`
  line
  line `Book 4, "Miscellaneous Register".`
  line
  line `B--In the offices of Registrars--`
  line
  line `Book 5, "Register of deposits of wills".`
  line
  line `(2) In Book 1 shall be entered or filed all documents or memoranda registered under sections 17, 18`
  line `and 89 which relate to immovable property, and are not wills.`
  line
  line `(3) In Book 4 shall be entered all documents registered under clauses (d) and (f) of section 18 which`
  line `do not relate to immovable property.`
  line
  line `(4) Nothing in this section shall be deemed to require more than one set of books where the office of`
  line `the Registrar has been amalgamated with the office of a Sub-Registrar.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENTS`
  line
  line Karnataka
  line
  line `Amendment of section 51.--In Section 51 of the principal Act, for clause (c) of sub-section (1),`
  line `the following clause shall be substituted, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) for sub-section (2), the following sub-section shall be substituted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"(2) In Book No.1 shall be filed,--`
  line
  line `(i) true copies of all documents; and`
  line
  line `(ii) all memoranda registered under sections 17, 18 and 89 which relate to immovable`
  line `property, and are not wills.";`
  line
  line `(b) in sub-section (3), for the words "entered all documents", the words "filed true copies of all`
  line `documents" shall be substituted;`
  line
  line `(c) after sub-section (4), the following sub-section shall be inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"(5) If, in the opinion of the Registrar, any of the books mentioned in sub-section (1) is in danger`
  line `of being destroyed, or becoming illegible wholly or partially, the Registrar may, by a written order,`
  line `direct such book or such portion thereof as he thinks fit, to be recopied and authenticated in such`
  line `manner as may be prescribed under section 69, and the copy prepared and authenticated under such`
  line `direction shall for the purposes of this Act, be deemed to have taken the place of and to be the`
  line `original book or portion and all references in this Act, to the original book or portion shall be deemed`
  line `to be references to the book or portion so prepared and authenticated."`
  line
  line `[Vide Karnataka Act 55 of 1976, s. 8]`
  line
  line Tripura--
  line
  line `Amendment of Section 51.--In section 51 of the principal Act,--`
  line
  line `(a) for sub-section (2), the following sub-section shall be substituted, namely:--`
  line
  line `(2) In Book I shall be`
  line
  line `(i) pasted true copied of all documents and`
  line
  line `(ii) filed all memoranda registered under Section 17, 18 and 89 which relate to immovable property, and`
  line `are not wills and`
  line
  line `(b) in sub-section (3), for the word "entered", the words "pasted true copies of" shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Tripura Act 7 of 1982, s. 6]`
  line
  line Kerala
  line
  line `Amendment of section 51.--In section 51 of the principal Act,--`
  line
  line `(a) for sub-section (2) the following sub-section shall be substituted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"(2) In Book I shall be filed---`
  line
  line `(i) true copies of all documents; and`
  line
  line `(ii) all memoranda,`
  line `Registered under sections 17, 18 and 89 which related to immovable property, and are not wills."`
  line
  line `(b) in sub-section (3), for the words "entered all documents", the words "filed true copies of all`
  line `documents" shall be substituted."`
  line
  line `[Vide kerala Act 7 of 1968, s. 7]`
  line
  line Orissa
  line
  line `Amendment of section 51.--In the Principal Act, in section 51,--`
  line
  line `(a) for sub-section (2), the following sub-section shall be substituted , namely:--`
  line
  line `"(2) In Book I shall be filed,--`
  line
  line `(i) true copies of all documents; and`
  line
  line `(ii) all memoranda registered under sections 17, 18 and 89 which relate to immovable`
  line `property and are not wills.";`
  line
  line `(b) in sub-section (3), for the "entered all documents", the words "filed true copies of all`
  line `documents", shall be substituted;`
  line
  line `(c) after sub-section (4), the following sub-section shall be inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"(5) If in the opinion of the Register any of the books mentioned in sub-section (1) is in`
  line `danger of being destroyed or becoming illegible wholly or partly, the registrar may, by written be`
  line `recopied and authenticated in such manner as may be prescribed under section 69 and the copy so`
  line `prepared and authenticated under such direction shall, for the purpose of this Act and of the`
  line `Evidence Act, 1872 be deemed to have taken the place of, and to be, the original book or`
  line `portion, as the case may be, and all references in this Act to the original book or portion shall be`
  line `deemed to be reference to the book or portion so prepared and authenticated.`
  line
  line `(6) Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, copies of any of the books mentioned in`
  line `sub-section (1) or any portion of such books prepared and authenticated before the`
  line `commencement of the Registration ( Orissa Amendment) Act, 1989 in pursuance of an order of`
  line `the Registrar or the Inspector-General of Registration, shall, for the purposes of this Act, and of`
  line `the Evidence Act, 1872 be deemed to have taken the place of, and to be, the original book or`
  line `portion, as the case may be, and all references in this Act to the original book or portion shall be`
  line `deemed to be references to the book or portion so prepared and authenticated".`
  line
  line `[Vide Orissa Act 14 of 1989, s. 6]`
obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_52:
  sectionId (37652)
  sectionNo (52)
  orderNo 55
  title `Duties of registering officers when document presented.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_52_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 48 of 2001, s. 7 (w.e.f. 24-9-2001).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338&sectionId=37652&sectionno=52&orderno=55&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338
obj_root_law_sections_52_content:
  string
  line `(1) (a) The day, hour and place of`
  line `presentation, ^1[the photographs and finger prints affixed under section 32A,] and the signature of every`
  line `person presenting a document for registration, shall be endorsed on every such document at the time of`
  line `presenting it;`
  line
  line `(b) a receipt for such document shall be given by the registering officer to the person presenting`
  line `the same; and`
  line
  line `(c) subject to the, provisions contained in section 62, every document admitted to registration`
  line `shall without unnecessary delay be copied in the book appropriated therefore according to the order`
  line `of its admission.`
  line
  line `(2) All such books shall be authenticated at such intervals and in such manner as is from time to time`
  line `prescribed by the Inspector-General.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENTS`
  line
  line Karnataka
  line
  line `Amendment of section 52.--In section 52 of the principal Act, for clause (c) of sub-section (1),`
  line `the following clause shall be substituted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"(c) subject to the provisions contained in section 62 where a document is admitted to`
  line `registration, a true copy thereof shall, without unnecessary delay, be filed in the appropriate book`
  line `according to the order of its admission".`
  line
  line `[Vide Karnataka Act 55 of 1976, s. 9]`
  line
  line Tripura--
  line
  line `Amendment of Section 52--In section 52 of the principal Act, for clause (c) of sub-section (1), the`
  line `following clause shall be substituted namely:--`
  line
  line `"(c) subject to the provisions contained in section 62 the true copy, referred to in section 18A of every`
  line `document admitted to registration shall, without unnecessary delay, be pasted in the book appropriated`
  line `therefore according to the order of its admission."`
  line
  line `[Vide Tripura Act 7 of 1982, s.7]`
  line
  line Kerala
  line
  line `Amendment of section 52.--In section 52 of the principal Act, for clause (c) of sub-section (1), the`
  line `following clause shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `"(c) subject to the provisions contained in section 62, where a document is admitted to`
  line `registration, a true copy thereof shall, without unnecessary delay, be filed in the appropriate book`
  line `according to the order of its admission."`
  line
  line `[Vide kerala Act 7 of 1968, s. 8]`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line `Himachal Pradesh`
  line
  line `5. Amendment of section 52.-- In section 52 of the principal Act, for clause (c) of sub-section (1),`
  line `the following clause shall be substituted, namely:-`
  line
  line `"(c) subject to the provisions contained in section 62, a copy of every document admitted to`
  line `registration shall, without unnecessary delay be pasted in the book appropriated therefore according`
  line `to the order of admission of the document."`
  line
  line `[Vide Himachal Pradesh Act 2 of 1969, s. 5]`
  line
  line Orissa
  line
  line `Amendment of section 52.-- In the principal Act, in section 52, for clause (c) of sub-section (1), the`
  line `following clause shall be substituted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"(c) subject to the provisions contained in section 62, where a document is admitted to`
  line `registration, a true copy thereof shall, without unnecessary delay, be filed in the appropriate book`
  line `according to its order of admission.".`
  line
  line `[Vide Orissa Act 14 of 1989, s. 7]`
obj_root_law_sections_53:
  sectionId (37653)
  sectionNo (53)
  orderNo 56
  title `Entries to be numbered consecutively.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_53_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338&sectionId=37653&sectionno=53&orderno=56&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338
obj_root_law_sections_53_content:
  string
  line `All entries in each book shall be numbered in a`
  line `consecutive series, which shall commence and terminate with the year, a fresh series being commenced at`
  line `the beginning of each year.`
obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_54:
  sectionId (37654)
  sectionNo (54)
  orderNo 57
  title `Current indexes and entries therein.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_54_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338&sectionId=37654&sectionno=54&orderno=57&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338
obj_root_law_sections_54_content:
  string
  line `In every office in which any of the books hereinbefore`
  line `mentioned are kept, there shall be prepared current indexes of the contents of such books; and every entry`
  line `in such indexes shall be made, so far as practicable, immediately after the registering officer has copied,`
  line `or filed a memorandum of, the document to which it relates.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENTS`
  line
  line Karnataka
  line
  line `Amendment of section 54.--In section 54 of the principal Act, for the words "copied, or filed`
  line `memorandum of, the words "filed a true copy or memorandum or shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Karnataka Act 55 of 1976, s. 10]`
  line
  line Tripura--
  line
  line `Amendment of Section 54.--In section 54 of the principal Act, for the words and mark "copied, or`
  line `filed a memorandum of "the words "pasted a true copy or filed a memorandum of" shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Tripura Act 7 of 1982, s. 8]`
  line
  line Kerala
  line
  line `Amendment of section 54.--In section 54 of the principal Act for the words "copied, or filed a`
  line `memorandum of, "the words "filed a true copy or memorandum of" shall be substituted."`
  line
  line `[Vide kerala Act 7 of 1968, s. 9]`
  line
  line Orissa
  line
  line `Amendment of section 54.-- In the principal Act, in section 54, for the words "copied or filed", the`
  line `words "filed a true copy or" shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Orissa Act 14 of 1989, s. 8]`
obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_55:
  sectionId (37655)
  sectionNo (55)
  orderNo 58
  title `Indexes to be made by registering officers, and their contents.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_55_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338&sectionId=37655&sectionno=55&orderno=58&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338
obj_root_law_sections_55_content:
  string
  line `(1) Four such indexes shall be`
  line `made in all registration offices, and shall be named, respectively, Index No. I, Index No. II, Index No. Ill`
  line `and Index No. IV.`
  line
  line `(2) Index No. I shall contain the names and additions of all persons executing and of all persons`
  line `claiming under every document entered or memorandum filed in Book No. 1.`
  line
  line `(3) Index No. II shall contain such particulars mentioned in section 21 relating to every such`
  line `document and memorandum as the Inspector-General from time to time directs in that behalf.`
  line
  line `(4) Index No. III shall contain the names and additions of all persons executing every will and`
  line `authority entered in Book No. 3, and of the executors and persons respectively appointed thereunder, and`
  line `after the death of the testator or the donor (but not before) the names and additions of all persons claiming`
  line `under the same.`
  line
  line `(5) Index No. IV shall contain the names and additions of all persons executing and of all persons`
  line `claiming under every document entered in Book No. 4.`
  line
  line `(6) Each Index shall contain such other particulars, and shall be prepared in such form, as the`
  line `Inspector-General from time to time directs.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENTS`
  line
  line Karnataka
  line
  line `Amendment of section 55.--In section 55 of the principal Act,--`
  line
  line `(a) in sub-section (2), for the words "documents entered or memorandum filed", the words`
  line `"documents of which a true copy or memorandum is filed" shall be substituted;`
  line
  line `(b) in sub-section (4), for the words "authority entered", the words "authority of which a true`
  line `copy is filed" shall be substituted;`
  line
  line `(c) in sub-section (5), for the words "document entered", the words "documents of which a true`
  line `copy is filed" shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Karnataka Act 55 of 1976, s. 11]`
  line
  line Tripura
  line
  line `Amendment of Section 55.--In section 55 of the principal Act--`
  line
  line `(a) in sub-section (2), for the word "entered" substitute the words "of which a true copy pasted";`
  line
  line `(b) in sub-section (4), for the words and figure "every will and authority entered in Book No. 3"`
  line `substitute the words and figure "every will and authority of which a true copy is pasted in Book No. 3";`
  line
  line `(c) in sub-section (5), for the word "entered" substitute the words "of which a true copy is pasted"`
  line `shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Tripura Act 7 of 1982, s. 9[`
  line
  line Kerala
  line
  line `Amendment of section 55.--In section 55 of the principal Act,--`
  line
  line `(a) in sub-section (2), for the words "document entered or memorandum filed", the words`
  line `"document of which a true copy, or memorandum, is filed" shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `(b) in sub-section (4), for the words "authority entered", the words "authority of which a true`
  line `copy is filed shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `(c) in sub-section (5), for the words "document entered", the words "document of which a true`
  line `copy is filed" shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `[Vide kerala Act 7 of 1968, s. 10]`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line Orissa
  line
  line `Amendment of section 55.-- In the principal Act, in section 55,--`
  line
  line `(a) in sub-section (2), for the words "document entered or memorandum filed", the words`
  line `document of which a true copy or a memorandum is filed" shall be substituted;`
  line
  line `(b) in sub-section (4), for the words "authority entered", the words "authority of which a true`
  line `copy is filed" shall be substituted; and`
  line
  line `(c) in sub-section (5), for the words "document entered", the words "document of which a true`
  line `copy is filed" shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Orissa Act 14 of 1989, s. 9]`
obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_56:
  sectionId (37656)
  sectionNo (56)
  orderNo 59
  title [Repealed.].
  content obj_root_law_sections_56_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338&sectionId=37656&sectionno=56&orderno=59&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338
obj_root_law_sections_56_content:
  string
  line `[Copy of entries in Indexes Nos. I, II and III to be sent by Sub-Registrar to Registrar and filed`
  line `(Repealed)] Rep. by the Indian Registration (Amendment) Act, 1929 (15 of 1929), s. 2.`
obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_57:
  sectionId (37694)
  sectionNo (57)
  orderNo 60
  title `Registering officers to allow inspection of certain books and indexes, and to give certified copies of entries.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_57_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338&sectionId=37694&sectionno=57&orderno=60&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338
obj_root_law_sections_57_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the previous payment of the fees payable in that behalf, the Books Nos.`
  line `1 and 2 and the Indexes relating to Book No. 1 shall be at all time open to inspection by any person`
  line `applying to inspect the same; and, subject to the provisions of section 62, copies or entries in such books`
  line `shall be given to all persons applying for such copies.`
  line
  line `(2) Subject to the same provisions, copies of entries in Book No. 3 and in the Index relating thereto`
  line `shall be given to the persons executing the documents to which such entries relate, or to their agents, and`
  line `after the death of the executants (but not before) to any person applying for such copies.`
  line
  line `(3) Subject to the same provisions, copies of entries in Book No. 4 and in the Index relating thereto`
  line `shall be given to any person executing or claiming under the documents to which such entries`
  line `respectively refer, or to his agent or representative.`
  line
  line `(4) The requisite search, under this section for entries in Book Nos. 3. and 4 shall be made only by the`
  line `registering officer.`
  line
  line `(5) All copies given under this section shall be signed and sealed by the registering officer, and shall`
  line `be admissible for the purpose of proving the contents of the original documents.`
obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_58:
  sectionId (37658)
  sectionNo (58)
  orderNo 61
  title `Particulars to be endorsed on documents admitted to registration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_58_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338&sectionId=37658&sectionno=58&orderno=61&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338
obj_root_law_sections_58_content:
  string
  line `(1) On every document`
  line `admitted to registration, other than a copy of a decree or order, or a copy sent to a registering officer`
  line `under section 89, there shall be endorsed from time to time the following particulars, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the signature and addition of every person admitting the execution of the document, and, if`
  line `such execution has been admitted by the representative, assign or agent of any person, the signature`
  line `and addition of such representative, assign or agent;`
  line
  line `(b) the signature and addition of every person examined in reference to such document under any`
  line `of the provisions of this Act; and`
  line
  line `(c) any payment of money or delivery of goods made in the presence of the registering officer in`
  line `reference to the execution of the document, and any admission of receipt of consideration, in whole or`
  line `in part, made in his presence in reference to such execution.`
  line
  line `(2) If any person admitting the execution of a document refuses to endorse the same, the registering`
  line `officer shall nevertheless register it, but shall at the same time endorse a note of such refusal.`
obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_59:
  sectionId (37659)
  sectionNo (59)
  orderNo 62
  title `Endorsements to be dated and signed by registering officer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_59_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338&sectionId=37659&sectionno=59&orderno=62&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338
obj_root_law_sections_59_content:
  string
  line `The registering officer shall`
  line `affix the date and his signature to all endorsements made under sections 52 and 58, relating to the`
  line `same document and made in his presence on the same day.`
obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_60:
  sectionId (37695)
  sectionNo (60)
  orderNo 63
  title `Certificate of registration`
  content obj_root_law_sections_60_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338&sectionId=37695&sectionno=60&orderno=63&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338
obj_root_law_sections_60_content:
  string
  line `(1) After such of the provisions of sections 34, 35, 58 and 59 as`
  line `apply to any document presented for registration have been complied with, the registering officer shall`
  line `endorse thereon a certificate containing the word registered, together with the number and page of the`
  line `book in which the document has been copied.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENTS`
  line
  line Karnataka
  line
  line `Amendment of section 60.--The words "the document has been copied ", the words "a true copy of`
  line `the document has been filed " shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Karnataka Act 55 of 1976, s. 12]`
  line
  line Kerala
  line
  line `Amendment of section 60.---In sub-section (1) of section 60, for the principal Act, for the words the`
  line `document has been copied", the words "the true copy of the document has been filed shall be`
  line substituted.]
  line
  line `[Vide kerala Act 7 of 1968, s. 11]`
  line
  line Orissa
  line
  line `Amendment of section 60.-- In the Principal Act, in sub-section (1) of section 60, for the words "the document has been copied ", the words "the true copy of the document has been filed " shall be`
  line substituted.
  line
  line `[Vide Orissa Act 14 of 1989, s. 10]`
  line
  line Tripura--
  line
  line `Amendment of Section 60.--In sub-section (1) of section 60 of the principal Act, for the words "the`
  line `document has been copied ", the words "the true copy of the document has been pasted " shall be`
  line substituted.
  line
  line `[Vide Tripura Act 7 of 1982, s. 10]`
obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_61:
  sectionId (37697)
  sectionNo (61)
  orderNo 64
  title `Endorsements and certificate to be copied and document returned.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_61_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_61_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338&sectionId=37697&sectionno=61&orderno=64&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338
obj_root_law_sections_61_content:
  string
  line `(1) The endorsements`
  line `and certificate referred to and mentioned in sections 59 and 60 shall thereupon be copied into the margin`
  line `of the Register-book, and the copy of the map or plan (if any) mentioned in section 21 shall be filed in`
  line `Book No. 1.`
  line
  line `(2) The registration of the document shall thereupon be deemed complete, and the document shall`
  line `then be returned to the person who presented the same for registration, or to such other person (if any) as`
  line `he has nominated in writing in that behalf on the receipt mentioned in section 52.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENTS`
  line
  line Karnataka
  line
  line `Amendment of section 61.--For sub-section (1) of section 61 of the principal Act the following`
  line `sub-section shall be substituted namely:--`
  line
  line `"(1) The endorsements and certificate referred to and mentioned in sections 59 and 60 shall`
  line `thereupon be copied into the true copy of the document presented along with the document and the`
  line `true copy of the map or the plan (if any) mentioned in section 21 shall also be filed along with the`
  line `true copy of the document."`
  line
  line `[Vide Karnataka Act 55 of 1976, s. 13]`
  line
  line Kerala
  line
  line `Amendment of section 61.--for sub-section (1) of section 61 of the principal Act, the following subsection shall be substitute, namely:--`
  line
  line `"(1) The endorsement and certificate referred to and mentioned in sections 59 and 60 shall`
  line `thereupon be copied into the true copy of the document presented along with the document, and the true copy of the map or plan (if any) mentioned in section 21 shall also be filed along with the true`
  line `copy of the document."`
  line
  line `[Vide kerala Act 7 of 1968, s. 12]`
  line
  line Orissa
  line
  line `Amendment of section 61.--In the principal Act, for sub-section (1) of section 61, the following`
  line `sub-section shall be substituted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"(1) The endorsements and certificates referred to and mentioned in sections 59 and 60 shall`
  line `thereupon be copied into the true copy of the document presented along with the document, and the`
  line `true copy of the map or plan, if any, mentioned in section 21 shall also be filed alongwith the true`
  line `copy of the document.".`
  line
  line `[Vide Orissa Act 14 of 1989, s. 11]`
  line
  line Tripura--
  line
  line `Amendment of section 61.--In sub-section (1) of the section 61 of the principal Act, the words "the`
  line `margin of" shall be omitted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Tripura Act 7 of 1982, s. 11]`
obj_root_law_sections_61_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_62:
  sectionId (37661)
  sectionNo (62)
  orderNo 65
  title `Procedure on presenting document in language unknown to registering officer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_62_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338&sectionId=37661&sectionno=62&orderno=65&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338
obj_root_law_sections_62_content:
  string
  line `(1) When a`
  line `document is presented for registration under section 19, the translation shall be transcribed in the register`
  line `of documents of the nature of the original, and, together with the copy referred to in section 19, shall be`
  line `filed in the registration office.`
  line
  line `(2) The endorsements and certificate respectively mentioned in sections 59 and 60 shall be made on`
  line `the original, and, for the purpose of making the copies and memoranda required by sections 57, 64, 65`
  line `and 66, the translation shall be treated as if it were the original.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENTS`
  line
  line Karnataka
  line
  line `Amendment of section 62.--For sub-section (1) of section 62 of the principal Act, the following`
  line `sub-section shall be substituted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"(1) When a document is presented for registration under section 19, the translation together with the`
  line `true copy of the document shall be filed in the appropriate book."`
  line
  line `[Vide Karnataka Act 55 of 1976, s. 14]`
  line
  line Kerala
  line
  line `Amendment of section 62.--For sub-section (1) of section 62 of the principal Act, the following subsection shall be substituted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"(1) When a document is presented for registration under section 19, the translation together with the`
  line `true copy of the document shall be filed in the appropriate book."`
  line
  line `[Vide kerala Act 7 of 1968, s. 13]`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line `Himachal Pradesh`
  line
  line `6. Amendment of section 62.- In section 62 of the principal Act, for sub-section (1), the following`
  line `sub-section shall be substituted, namely:-`
  line
  line `"(1) When a document is presented for registration under section 19, a copy of the translation shall`
  line `be pasted in the register of documents of the nature of the original, and the second copy of the`
  line `translation, together with the true copy referred to in Section 19, shall be filed in the registration office."`
  line
  line `[Vide Himachal Pradesh Act 2 of 1969, s. 6]`
  line
  line Orissa
  line
  line `Amendment of section 62.-- In the principal Act, for sub-section (1) of section 62, the following`
  line `sub-section shall be substituted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"(1) when a document is presented for registration under section 19, the translation together with`
  line `the true copy of the document shall be filed in the "appropriate book.".`
  line
  line `[Vide Orissa Act 14 of 1989, s. 12]`
  line
  line Tripura--
  line
  line `Amendment of section 62.--In section 62 of the principal Act, for sub-section (1), the following shall be`
  line `substituted:--`
  line
  line `"when a document is presented for registration under section 19, the true translation together with the`
  line `true copy referred to in that section shall be pasted in the register of documents of the nature of the`
  line `original and the second copy of the translation shall be filed with Registration Office".`
  line
  line `[Vide Tripura Act 7 of 1982, s. 12]`
obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_63:
  sectionId (37662)
  sectionNo (63)
  orderNo 66
  title `Power to administer oaths and record of substance of statements.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_63_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_63_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338&sectionId=37662&sectionno=63&orderno=66&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338
obj_root_law_sections_63_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every registering`
  line `officer may, at his discretion, administer an oath to any person examined by him under the provisions of`
  line `this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every such officer may also at his discretion record a note of the substance of the statement made`
  line `by each such person, and such statement shall be read over, or (if made in a language with which such`
  line `person is not acquainted) interpreted to him in a language with which he is acquainted, and, if he admits`
  line `the correctness of such note, it shall be signed by the registering officer.`
  line
  line `(3) Every such note so signed shall be admissible for the purpose of proving that the statements`
  line `therein recorded were made by the persons and under the circumstances therein stated.`
obj_root_law_sections_63_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_64:
  sectionId (37663)
  sectionNo (64)
  orderNo 67
  title `Procedure where document relates to land in several sub-districts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_64_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_64_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338&sectionId=37663&sectionno=64&orderno=67&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338
obj_root_law_sections_64_content:
  string
  line `Every Sub-Registrar on`
  line `registering a non-testamentary document relating to immovable property not wholly situate in his own`
  line `sub-district shall make a memorandum thereof and of the endorsement and certificate (if any) thereon,`
  line `and send the same to every other Sub-Registrar subordinate to the same Registrar as himself in whose`
  line `sub-district any part of such property is situate, and such Sub-Registrar shall file the memorandum in his`
  line `Book No. 1.`
obj_root_law_sections_64_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_65:
  sectionId (37664)
  sectionNo (65)
  orderNo 68
  title `Procedure where document relates to land in several districts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_65_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_65_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338&sectionId=37664&sectionno=65&orderno=68&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338
obj_root_law_sections_65_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every Sub-Registrar on`
  line `registering a non-testamentary document relating to immovable property situate in more districts than one`
  line `shall also forward a copy thereof and of the endorsement and certificate (if any) thereon, together with a`
  line `copy of the map or plan (if any) mentioned in section 21, to the Registrar of every district in which any`
  line `part of such property is situate other than the district in which his own sub-district is situate.`
  line
  line `(2) The Registrar on receiving the same shall file in his Book No. 1 the copy of the document and the`
  line `copy of the map or plan (if any), and shall forward a memorandum of the document to each of the SubRegistrars subordinate to him within whose sub-district any part of such property is situate; and every`
  line `Sub-Registrar receiving such memorandum shall file in his Book No. 1.`
obj_root_law_sections_65_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_66:
  sectionId (37665)
  sectionNo (66)
  orderNo 69
  title `Procedure after registration of documents relating to land.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_66_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338&sectionId=37665&sectionno=66&orderno=69&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338
obj_root_law_sections_66_content:
  string
  line `(1) On registering any nontestamentary document relating to immovable properly, the Registrar shall forward a memorandum of`
  line `such document to each Sub-Registrar subordinate to himself in whose sub-district any part of the property`
  line `is situate.`
  line
  line `(2) The Registrar shall also forward a copy of such document, together with a copy of the map or plan`
  line `(if any) mentioned in section 21, to every other Registrar in whose district any part of such property is`
  line situate.
  line
  line `(3) Such Registrar on receiving any such copy shall file it in his Book No. 1, and shall also send a`
  line `memorandum of the copy to each of the Sub-Registrars subordinate to him within whose sub-district any`
  line `part of the property is situate.`
  line
  line `(4) Every Sub-Registrar receiving any memorandum under this section shall file it in his Book No. 1.`
obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_67:
  sectionId (37666)
  sectionNo (67)
  orderNo 70
  title [Omitted.].
  content obj_root_law_sections_67_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_67_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338&sectionId=37666&sectionno=67&orderno=70&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338
obj_root_law_sections_67_content:
  string
  line `[Procedure after registration under section 30, sub-section (2).] Omitted by the Registration and`
  line `Other Related Laws (Amendment) Act, 2001 (48 of 2001), s. 8 (w.e.f. 24-9-2001).`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line Karnataka
  line
  line `Omission of section 67.-Section 67 of the principal Act, shall be omitted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Karnataka Act 24 of 1989, s. 3]`
  line
  line Rajasthan
  line
  line `Amendment of section 67, Central Act 16 of 1908.-Section 67 of the principal Act shall be omitted.`
  line
  line `[Vide ajasthan Act 18 of 1989, s. 5]`
  line
  line Haryana
  line
  line `Omission of section 67 of Central Act 16 of 1908.--Section 67 of the principal Act shall be omitted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Haryana Act 4 of 1997, s. 3]`
obj_root_law_sections_67_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_68:
  sectionId (37667)
  sectionNo (68)
  orderNo 71
  title `Power of Registrar to superintend and control Sub-Registrars.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_68_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_68_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338&sectionId=37667&sectionno=68&orderno=71&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338
obj_root_law_sections_68_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every Sub-Registrar`
  line `shall perform the duties of his office under the superintendence and control of the Registrar in whose`
  line `district the office of such Sub-Registrar is situate.`
  line
  line `(2) Every Registrar shall have authority to issue (whether on complaint or otherwise) any order`
  line `consistent with this Act which he considers necessary in respect of any act or omission of any SubRegistrar subordinate to him or in respect of the rectification of any error regarding the book or the office`
  line `in which any document has been registered.`
obj_root_law_sections_68_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_69:
  sectionId (37668)
  sectionNo (69)
  orderNo 72
  title `Power of Inspector-General to superintend registration offices and make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_69_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_69_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338&sectionId=37668&sectionno=69&orderno=72&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338
obj_root_law_sections_69_content:
  string
  line `(1) The`
  line `Inspector-General shall exercise a general superintendence over all the registration offices in the`
  line `territories under the ^1[State Government], and shall have power from time to time to make rules consistent`
  line `with this Act--`
  line
  line `(a) providing for the safe custody of books, papers and documents;`
  line ^2***
  line
  line `^3[(aa) providing the manner in which and the safeguards subject to which the books may be kept`
  line `in computer floppies or diskettes or in any other electronic form under sub-section (1) of section`
  line 16A;]
  line
  line `(b) declaring what language shall be deemed to be commonly used in each district;`
  line
  line `(c) declaring what territorial divisions shall be recognized under section 21;`
  line
  line `(d) regulating the amount of fines imposed under sections 25 and 34, respectively;`
  line
  line `(e) regulating the exercise of the discretion reposed in the registering officer by section 63;`
  line
  line `(f) regulating the form in which registering officers are to make memoranda of documents;`
  line
  line `(g) regulating the authentication by Registrars and Sub-Registrars of the books kept in their`
  line `respective offices under section 51;`
  line
  line `^4[(gg) regulating the manner in which the instruments referred to in sub-section (2) of section 88`
  line `may be presented for registration;]`
  line
  line `(h) declaring the particulars to be contained in Indexes Nos. I, II, III and IV, respectively;`
  line
  line `(i) declaring the holidays that shall be observed in the registration offices; and`
  line
  line `(j) generally, regulating the proceedings of the Registrars and Sub-Registrars.`
  line
  line `(2) The rules so made shall be submitted to the ^1[State Government] for approval, and, after they have`
  line `been approved, they shall be published in the ^5[Official Gazette], and on publication shall have effect as if`
  line `enacted in this Act.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENTS`
  line
  line Karnataka
  line
  line `Amendment of section 69.--In sub-section (1) of section 69 of the principal Act,`
  line `(i) in clause (g) after the word and figures "section 51", insert the words and the manner of`
  line `recopying such books on portions thereof,`
  line
  line `(ii) after clause (i) insert us under--`
  line
  line `(ii) prescribing the manner in which and the terms subject to which persons who write deeds`
  line `outside the precincts of a registration officer, or who frequent the precincts of registration`
  line `officers, for the purpose of writing documents may be granted licence and prescribing the fees to`
  line `be paid for such licences;`
  line
  line `[Vide Karnataka Act 55 of 1976, s. 15]`
  line
  line Kerala
  line
  line `Amendment of section 69.--After clause (b) of sub-section (1) of section 69 of the principal Act, the`
  line `following clause shall be inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"(bb) providing for the grant of licences to document writers, the revocation of such licences the`
  line `terms and conditions subject to which and the authority by whom such licences shall be granted and`
  line `generally for all purposes connected with the writing of documents to be presented for registration."`
  line
  line `[Vide Kerala Act 2 of 1959, s. 3]`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line `Himachal Pradesh`
  line
  line `7. Amendment of section 69.- In section 69 of the principal Act, in sub-section (1), after clause`
  line `(b), the following clause shall be inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"(bb) providing for the grant of licences to document writers, the revocation of such licences, the`
  line `terms and conditions subject to which, and the authority by whom such licences shall be ranted and`
  line `generally for all purposes connected with the writing of the documents to be presented for`
  line `registration."`
  line
  line `[Vide Himachal Pradesh Act 2 of 1969, s. 7]`
  line
  line Orissa
  line
  line `Amendment of section 69.--In section 69 of the Registration Act, 1908 (16 of 1908), in sub-section`
  line `(1) after clause (b), the following new clause shall be inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"(bb) providing for the grant of licences, the terms and conditions subject to which and the`
  line `authority by whom such licences shall be granted, the exemption of any class of document writers`
  line `from the licensing provisions and the conditions subject to which such exemption shall be granted`
  line `and generally for all purposes connected with the writing of documents to be presented for`
  line `registration.".`
  line
  line `[Vide Orissa Act 11 of 1976, s. 2]`
  line
  line Tripura
  line
  line `Amendment of Section 69.--In section 69 of the principal Act, in sub-section (1) after clause (b), the`
  line `following clause be inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"(bb) providing for the grant and renewal of licences to document writers, the revocation of`
  line `licences granted to such writers and generally for all purposes connected with the writers and`
  line `generally for all purposes connected with the writing of the documents and with the writing of`
  line `the true copies of the documents to be presented for registration".`
  line
  line `[Vide Tripura Act 7 of 1982, s. 13]`
  line
  line Uttarkhand
  line
  line `Insertion of section 69.--In section 69 of the Principal Act, after clause (hh), the following clauses shall be inserted, namely:-`
  line
  line `(hh-1) regulating the number and manner in which printouts or true copies of documents and of translation shall be prepared and the Books in which they shall be kept for record;`
  line `(hh-2) regulating the form of declaration and the manner of comparison and verification of the true copies;`
  line
  line `(hh-3) regulating the manner in which and safeguards subject to which the Books may be kept in electronic form.`
  line
  line `(2) After section 69 of the Principal Act, the following section shall be inserted, namely:-`
  line
  line `69-A Notwithstanding anything contained in any other provisions of this Act, the Inspector-General of Registration shall with the prior approval of the State Government, prepare and circulate standard formats of various kinds of documents for the guidance of the general public, which may be used with or without modifications.`
  line
  line `Explanation:- Use of a standard format prepared and circulated under this section shall not be a prelude to omit the descriptions of the property required under sections 21 and 22.`
  line
  line `[Vide Uttarakhand Act 24 of 2014, s. 22]`
  line
  line Rajasthan
  line
  line `Amendment of section 69, Act XVI of 1908.- After clause (b) of sub-section (1) of section 69 of the Indian Registration Act, 1908 (XVI of 1908), the following clause shall be inserted, namely:-`
  line
  line `"(bb) providing for the grant of licences to document writers, the revocation of such licences, the terms and conditions subject to which and the authority by whom such licences shall be granted and generally for all purposes connected with the writing of documents to be presented for registration".`
  line
  line `[Vide Rajasthan Act XVIII of 1953, s. 2]`
  line
  line Rajasthan
  line
  line `Amendment of section 69, Central Act 16 of 1908.-After sub-section(2) of section 69 of the principal Act, the following shall be added, namely:-`
  line
  line `(3) The Inspector-General shall have power to issue any order consistent with this Act which he considers necessary in respect of any act or omission of any person subordinate to him or in respect of rectification of any error regarding the book or the office in which any document has been registered..`
  line
  line `[VideRajasthan Act 18 of 1989, s. 6]`
  line
  line Gujarat
  line
  line `Amendment of section 69 of XVI of 1908.-- In the principal Act, in section 69,insub-section (1),after clause (j), the following clause shall be added, namely:-`
  line
  line `"(k) regulating the procedure for presentation of document, appearance for admission, endorsement, manner of affixing signature and seal, mode of payment of registration fees and other fees and such other process when the document is presented by electronic means."`
  line
  line `[Vide Gujarat Act 4 of 2020, s. 6]`
obj_root_law_sections_69_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for Provincial Government.`
  line
  line `2. The words and also for the destruction of such books, papers and documents as need no longer be kept rep. by Act 5 of`
  line `1917, s. 6 and the Schedule.`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 48 of 2001, s. 9 (w.e.f. 24-9-2001).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by Act 39 of 1948, s. 4.`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "Local Official Gazette".`
obj_root_law_sections_70:
  sectionId (37669)
  sectionNo (70)
  orderNo 73
  title `Power of Inspector-General to remit fines.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_70_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_70_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338&sectionId=37669&sectionno=70&orderno=73&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338
obj_root_law_sections_70_content:
  string
  line `The Inspector-General may also, in the exercise of`
  line `his discretion, remit wholly or in part the difference between any fine levied under section 25 or section`
  line `34, and the amount of the proper registration fee.`
obj_root_law_sections_70_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_71:
  sectionId (37670)
  sectionNo (71)
  orderNo 74
  title `Reasons for refusal to register to be recorded.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_71_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_71_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338&sectionId=37670&sectionno=71&orderno=74&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338
obj_root_law_sections_71_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every Sub-Registrar refusing to register`
  line `a document, except on the ground that the property to which it relates is not situate within his sub-district,`
  line `shall make an order of refusal and record his reasons for such order in his Book No. 2, and endorse the`
  line `words "registration refused" on the document; and, on application made by any person executing or`
  line `claiming under the document, shall, without payment and unnecessary delay, give him a copy of the`
  line `reasons so recorded.`
  line
  line `(2) No registering officer shall accept for registration a document so endorsed unless and until, under`
  line `the provisions hereinafter contained, the document is directed to be registered.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line Kerala
  line
  line `Amendment of section 71.--In section 71 of the principal Act, after sub-section (2), the following`
  line `sub-section shall be inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"(3) No registering officer shall accept for registration any document involving transfer of`
  line `property including contract for sale of immovable property belonging to or vested in the Government`
  line `of Kerala or public sector undertakings operating in the State or local self government institutions`
  line `unless it is accompanied by a no objection certificate issued by an officer authorised by the State`
  line `Government in this behalf.".`
  line
  line `[Vide Kerala Act 31 of 2013, s. 3]`
obj_root_law_sections_71_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_72:
  sectionId (37698)
  sectionNo (72)
  orderNo 75
  title `Appeal to Registrar from orders of Sub-Registrar refusing registration on ground other than denial of execution.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_72_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_72_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338&sectionId=37698&sectionno=72&orderno=75&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338
obj_root_law_sections_72_content:
  string
  line `(1) Except where the refusal is made on the ground of denial of execution, an`
  line `appeal shall lie against an order of a Sub-Registrar refusing to admit a document to registration (whether`
  line `the registration of such document is compulsory or optional) to the Registrar to whom such Sub-Registrar`
  line `is subordinate, if presented to such Registrar within thirty days from the date of the order; and the`
  line `Registrar may reverse or alter such order.`
  line
  line `(2) If the order of the Registrar directs the document to be registered and the document is duly`
  line `presented for registration within thirty days after the making of such order, the Sub-Registrar shall obey`
  line `the same, and thereupon shall, so far as may be practicable, follow the procedure prescribed in sections`
  line `58, 59 and 60; and such registration shall take effect as if the document had been registered when it was`
  line `first duly presented for registration.`
obj_root_law_sections_72_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_73:
  sectionId (37672)
  sectionNo (73)
  orderNo 76
  title `Application to Registrar where Sub-Registrar refuses to register on ground of denial of execution.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_73_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_73_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338&sectionId=37672&sectionno=73&orderno=76&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338
obj_root_law_sections_73_content:
  string
  line `(1) When a Sub-Registrar has refused to register a document on the ground that any person`
  line `by whom it purports to be executed, or his representative or assign, denies its execution, any person`
  line `claiming under such document, or his representative, assign or agent authorised as aforesaid, may, within`
  line `thirty days after the making of the order of refusal, apply to the Registrar to whom such Sub-Registrar is`
  line `subordinate in order to establish his right to have the document registered.`
  line
  line `(2) Such application shall be in writing and shall be accompanied by a copy of the reasons recorded`
  line `under section 71, and the statements in the application shall be verified by the applicant in manner`
  line `required by law for the verification of plaints.`
obj_root_law_sections_73_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_74:
  sectionId (37673)
  sectionNo (74)
  orderNo 77
  title `Procedure of Registrar on such application.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_74_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_74_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338&sectionId=37673&sectionno=74&orderno=77&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338
obj_root_law_sections_74_content:
  string
  line `In such case, and also where such denial as`
  line `aforesaid is made before a Registrar in respect of a document presented for registration to him, the`
  line `Registrar shall, as soon as conveniently may be, enquire.--`
  line
  line `(a) whether the document has been executed;`
  line
  line `(b) whether the requirements of the law for the time being in force have been complied with on`
  line `the part of the applicant or person presenting the document for registration, as the case may be, so as`
  line `to entitle the document to registration.`
obj_root_law_sections_74_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_75:
  sectionId (37674)
  sectionNo (75)
  orderNo 78
  title `Order by Registrar to register and procedure thereon.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_75_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_75_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338&sectionId=37674&sectionno=75&orderno=78&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338
obj_root_law_sections_75_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the Registrar finds that the`
  line `document has been executed and that the said requirements have been complied with, he shall order the`
  line `document to be registered.`
  line
  line `(2) If the document is duly presented for registration within thirty days after the making of such order,`
  line `the registering officer shall obey the same and thereupon shall, so far as may be practicable, follow the`
  line `procedure prescribed in sections 58, 59 and 60.`
  line
  line `(3) Such registration shall take effect as if the document had been registered when it was first duly`
  line `presented for registration.`
  line
  line `(4) The Registrar may, for the purpose of any enquiry under section 74, summon and enforce the`
  line `attendance of witness, and compel them to give evidence, as if he were a Civil Court and he may also`
  line `direct by whom the whole or any part of the costs of any such enquiry shall be paid, and such costs shall`
  line `be recoverable as if they had been awarded in a suit under the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908).`
obj_root_law_sections_75_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_76:
  sectionId (37675)
  sectionNo (76)
  orderNo 79
  title `Order of refusal by Registrar.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_76_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_76_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338&sectionId=37675&sectionno=76&orderno=79&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338
obj_root_law_sections_76_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every Registrar refusing--`
  line
  line `(a) to register a document except on the ground that the property to which it relates is not situate`
  line `within his district or that the document ought to be registered in the office of a Sub-Registrar, or`
  line
  line `(b) to direct the registration of a document under section 72 or section 75,`
  line
  line `shall make an order of refusal and record the reasons for such order in his Book No. 2, and, on application`
  line `made by any person executing or claiming under the document, shall, without unnecessary delay, give`
  line `him a copy of the reasons so recorded.`
  line
  line `(2) No appeal lies from any order by a Registrar under this section or section 72.`
obj_root_law_sections_76_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_77:
  sectionId (37676)
  sectionNo (77)
  orderNo 80
  title `Suit in case of order of refusal by Registrar.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_77_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_77_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338&sectionId=37676&sectionno=77&orderno=80&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338
obj_root_law_sections_77_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the Registrar refuses to order the`
  line `document to be registered, under section 72 or a decree section 76, any person claiming under such`
  line `document, or his representative, assign or agent, may, within thirty days after the making of the order of`
  line `refusal, institute in the Civil Court, within the local limits of whose original jurisdiction is situate the`
  line `office in which the document is sought to be registered, a suit for a decree directing the document to be`
  line `registered in such office if it be duly presented for registration within thirty days after the passing of such`
  line decree.
  line
  line `(2) The provisions contained in sub-sections (2) and (3) of section 75 shall, mutatis mutandis, apply`
  line `to all documents presented for registration in accordance with any such decree, and, notwithstanding`
  line `anything contained in this Act, the documents shall be receivable in evidence in such suit.`
obj_root_law_sections_77_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_78:
  sectionId (37677)
  sectionNo (78)
  orderNo 81
  title `Fees to be fixed by State Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_78_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_78_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338&sectionId=37677&sectionno=78&orderno=81&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338
obj_root_law_sections_78_content:
  string
  line `^1*** The ^2[State Government] shall prepare a table of`
  line `fees payable--`
  line
  line `(a) for the registration of documents;`
  line
  line `(b) for searching the registers;`
  line
  line `(c) for making or granting copies of reasons, entries or documents, before on or after registration;`
  line
  line `and of extra or additional fees payable`
  line
  line `(d) for every registration under section 30;`
  line
  line `(e) for the issue of commissions;`
  line
  line `(f) for filing translations;`
  line
  line `(g) for attending at private residences;`
  line
  line `(h) for the safe custody and return of document; and`
  line
  line `(i) for such other matters as appear to the Government necessary to effect the purposes of this`
  line Act.
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENTS`
  line
  line Assam
  line
  line `Insertion of new Section 78A.-- In the principal Act, after the existing sections 78, the following new`
  line `section 78A shall be inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `78A. Power to reduce or remit fees.--The State Government may, if in its opinion it is`
  line `necessary in the public interest so to do, by order published in the Official Gazette, reduce or remit the fees payable in respect of any of the matters enumerated in clauses (a) to (i) of section 78, either`
  line `generally or for any particular class of cases and in respect of persons generally or of any particular`
  line `class or classes of persons, or in respect of any particular class or classes of instruments.`
  line
  line `[Vide Assam Act 24 of 2013, s. 2]`
  line
  line Kerala
  line
  line `Amendment of section 78.--Section 78 of the principal Act shall be renumbered as sub-section (1) of`
  line `that section, and after sub-section (1) as so renumbered, the following sub-section shall be inserted,`
  line `namely:--`
  line
  line `(2) The State Government may, if in their opinion it is necessary in the public interest so to do, by`
  line `order published in the Official Gazette, remit the fees payable in respect of any of the matters encumbered`
  line `in clauses (a) to (i) of sub-section (1), either generally for any particular class or classes of cases and in`
  line `respect of persons generally or of any particular class or classes of persons.`
  line
  line `[Vide kerala Act 7 of 1968, s. 14]`
  line
  line Orissa
  line
  line `Insertion of new section 78-A.--After section 78 of the principal Act, the following section shall be`
  line `inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `78-A. Power to remit fees.--The State Government, if it is of the opinion that any instrument`
  line `which involves donation of property for public charitable purpose, or involves exchange of land on`
  line `the initiative of the State Government in the public interest, may, by order published in the Gazette,`
  line `remit the fees payable in respect of any such instrument.`
  line
  line `[Vide Orissa Act 8 of 2002, s. 7]`
  line
  line Uttarakhand
  line
  line `Insertion of section 78-B.After section 78-A of the Principal Act, the following section shall be inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `78-B (1) The fee for the registration of a document may be charged in the form of adhesive labels for which the Inspector-General of Registration may, with the prior approval of the State Government, make rules to regulate supply and sale thereof, the persons by whom alone such sale is to be conducted and the duties and remuneration of and the fees chargeable from such persons.`
  line
  line `(2) The District Registrar may, on an application of a person, make allowance for the spoiled, misused or unused adhesive labels purchased for the registration of a document is accordance with the rules made by the Inspector-General of Registration with the prior approval of the State Government.`
  line
  line `[Vide Uttarakhand Act 24 of 2014, s. 23]`
  line
  line Rajasthan
  line
  line `Amendment of section 78, Central Act XVI of 1908. Section 78 of the principal Act shall be renumbered as sub-section (1) thereof and after sub-section (1), as so re-numbered, the following sub-section shall be added namely:-`
  line
  line `(2) The State Government may, if in its opinion it is necessary in the public interest so to do, by order published in the official Gazette, remit or reduce the fees payable in respect of any of the matters enumerated in clauses (a) to (i) of sub-section (1), either generally or for any particular class or classes of cases and in respect of persons generally or of any particular class or classes of persons.`
  line
  line `[Vide Rajasthan Act 16 of 1976, s. 4]`
obj_root_law_sections_78_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words Subject to the control of the Governor-General in Council omitted by Act 38 of 1920, s. 2, and the First Schedule.`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for Provincial Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_79:
  sectionId (37678)
  sectionNo (79)
  orderNo 82
  title `Publication of fees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_79_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_79_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338&sectionId=37678&sectionno=79&orderno=82&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338
obj_root_law_sections_79_content:
  string
  line `A table of the fees so payable shall be published in the Official Gazette,`
  line `and a copy thereof in English and the vernacular language of the district shall be exposed to public view`
  line `in every registration office.`
obj_root_law_sections_79_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_80:
  sectionId (37679)
  sectionNo (80)
  orderNo 83
  title `Fees payable on presentation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_80_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_80_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338&sectionId=37679&sectionno=80&orderno=83&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338
obj_root_law_sections_80_content:
  string
  line `All fees for the registration of documents under this Act shall be`
  line `payable on the presentation of such documents.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENTS`
  line
  line Kerala
  line
  line `Insertion of new section 80 A.--After section 80 of the Registration Act, 1908 (Central Act 16 of`
  line `1908), the following section shall be inserted, namely.--`
  line
  line `"80A. Recovery of registration fees in certain cases.--If on inspection or otherwise it is found that`
  line `the fee payable under this Act in relation to any document which is registered has not been paid or has`
  line `been insufficiently paid or that the fee paid has subsequently been found to be insufficient due to the fact`
  line `that the value of the property or the consideration, as the case may be, has not been truly set forth in the`
  line `document, such fee or the difference between the fee paid and the fee due, as the case may be, may on a`
  line `certificate by the Inspector General of Registration or an officer authorised by him in that behalf, be`
  line `recovered from the person who presented such document for registration under section 32, as an arrear of`
  line `public revenue due on land under the provisions of the Revenue Recovery Act for the time being in force:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such certificate shall be granted unless enquiry in the prescribed manner has been`
  line `held and such person has been given a reasonable opportunity of being heard:`
  line
  line `Provided further that no such certificate shall be granted after the expiry of a period of three years`
  line `from the date of presentation of the document under section 32.".`
  line
  line `[Vide Kerala Act 21 of 1998, s. 2]`
  line
  line Karnataka
  line
  line `Insertion of new section 80A.--After section 80 of the Registration Act, 1908 (Central Act 16 of`
  line `1908) the following section shall be inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"80A. Deficient amount of fees payable and their recovery.--(1) If the value of the property`
  line `has been increased under section 45A of the Karnataka Stamp Act, 1957 (Karnataka Act 34 of 1957),`
  line `consequential increase in the fee for the registration of documents under this Act shall be paid by the`
  line `person liable to pay the same within a period of thirty days from the date, the order determining the`
  line `market value of the property is communicated to him.`
  line
  line `(2) The fee payable under sub-section (1) may be recovered as an arrear of land revenue."`
  line
  line `Vide Karnataka Act 28 of 1975, s. 2]`
  line
  line Karnataka
  line
  line `Insertion of new Part after Part XIII--After Part XIII of the principal Act, the following Part shall be`
  line `inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `PART XIII-A`
  line
  line `OF DEED WRITERS`
  line
  line `80B. Deed Writers to hold licences.--No person other than an advocate or other legal`
  line `practitioner, shall for payment, write deeds unless he holds a licence granted in accordance with rules`
  line `made under section 69".`
  line
  line `[Vide Karnataka Act 55 of 1976, s. 16]`
  line
  line Karnataka
  line
  line `Insertion of new section 80A.--After section 80 of the Registration Act, 1908 (Central Act 25 of`
  line `1908), the following section shall be and shall be deemed to have been inserted with effect from the`
  line `first day of April, 1972, namely:--`
  line
  line `"80A. Recovery of registration fee not levied or short levied, etc.--(1) If on inspection or`
  line `otherwise, it is found that the fee payable under this Act in relation to any document which is`
  line `registered has not been paid or has been insufficiently paid, such fee may, on a certificate of the`
  line `Inspector-General of Registration, be recovered from the person who presented such document`
  line `for registration, as an arrear of land revenue. The certificate of the Inspector-General shall be`
  line `final and shall not be called in question in any court or before any authority:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such certificate shall be granted without giving such person,--`
  line
  line `(i) an opportunity of being heard; and`
  line
  line `(ii) an opportunity to pay the amount of fee found due from him.`
  line
  line `(2) If on inspection or otherwise the Inspector-General of Registration finds that the amount`
  line `of fees charged and paid under the provisions of this Act is in excess of that which is legally`
  line `chargeable, he may, upon an application in writing or otherwise, refund the excess fee so charged`
  line `and paid.`
  line
  line `(3) Nothing in sub-sections (1) and (2) shall apply to instruments executed prior to first day`
  line `of April, 1972."`
  line
  line `[Vide Karnataka Act 19 of 1980, s. 2]`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line `Himachal Pradesh`
  line
  line `Insertion of new section 80-A.- In the Registration Act, 1908 (16 of 1908) after section 80,`
  line `the following new section along with its heading shall be inserted and shall be deemed always to have`
  line `been inserted, namely:-`
  line
  line `"80-A. Recovery of registration fee as arrears of land revenue and provision for refund.- (l)`
  line `If on inspection, or otherwise, it is found that the fee payable under this Act in relation to any`
  line `document which is registered has not been paid or has been insufficiently paid, such fee may, after`
  line `failure to pay the same on demand within a specified period, on a certificate of the registering`
  line `authority concerned, be recovered from the person who presented such document for registration`
  line `under section 32 as an arrear of land revenue.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the Registrar finds the amount of fee in excess of that which is legally chargeable has`
  line `been charged and paid under the provisions of this Act, he may, upon an application in writing or`
  line `otherwise, refund the excess."`
  line
  line `[Vide Himachal Pradesh Act 1 of 1982, s. 2]`
  line
  line Orissa
  line
  line `Insertion of new section 80-A.-- In the principal Act, after section 80, the following section shall be`
  line `inserted namely:--`
  line
  line `"80-A. Recovery of deficient registration fee as arrears of land revenue.--If, on inspection or`
  line `otherwise, it is found that the fee payable under this Act in relation to any document which is registered`
  line `has been insufficiently paid, the deficient fee shall, after failure to pay the same on demand within the`
  line `prescribed period, be recoverable from the person who presented such document as arrears of land`
  line `revenue.".`
  line
  line `[Vide Orissa Act 19 of 1991, s. 3]`
  line
  line Haryana
  line
  line `Insertion of section 80A in Central Act 16 of 1908.--After section 80 of the Registration Act, 1908, the`
  line `following new section shall be inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"80A. Deficient amounts of fees payable and their recovery.--(1) If the value of the property`
  line `or the consideration, as the case may be, has been increased under section 47A of the Indian Stamp`
  line `Act, 1899, the consequential increase in the fee for the registration of documents under this Act, shall`
  line `be paid by the person liable to pay the same within a period of thirty days from the date the order of`
  line `determination of the value of the property or the consideration, as the case may be, is communicated`
  line `to him.`
  line
  line `(2) The fee payable under sub-section (1) may be recovered as an arrear of land revenue.".`
  line
  line `[Vide Haryana Act 36 of 1973, s. 2]`
obj_root_law_sections_80_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_81:
  sectionId (37699)
  sectionNo (81)
  orderNo 84
  title `Penalty for incorrectly endorsing, copying, translating or registering documents with intent to injure.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_81_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_81_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338&sectionId=37699&sectionno=81&orderno=84&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338
obj_root_law_sections_81_content:
  string
  line `Every registering officer appointed under this Act and every person employed in his office`
  line `for the purposes of this Act, who, being charged with the endorsing, copying, translating or registering of`
  line `any document presented or deposited under its provisions, endorses, copies, translates or registers such`
  line `document in a manner which he knows or believes to be incorrect, intending thereby to cause or knowing`
  line `it to be likely that he may thereby cause, injury, as defined in the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860), to any`
  line `person, shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to seven years, or with fine,`
  line `or with both.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENTS`
  line
  line Karnataka
  line
  line `Amendment of section 81.--In section 81 of the principal Act,--`
  line
  line `(i) in the marginal heading, for the words "the registering", the words "registering or filing" shall`
  line `be substituted;`
  line
  line `(ii) for the words "or registering of any document the words registering or filing a true copy of`
  line `any document shall be substituted;`
  line
  line `(iii) for the words "or registers such document", the words "registers or files a copy of such`
  line `document" shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Karnataka Act 55 of 1976, s. 17]`
  line
  line Kerala
  line
  line `Amendment of section 81.--In section 81 of the principal Act,--`
  line
  line `(a) for the words "or registering of any document", the words registering, or filing a true copy,`
  line `of any document" shall be substituted;`
  line
  line `(b) for the words "or registers such document", the words "registers, or files a true copy of, such`
  line `document" shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Kerala Act 7 of 1968, s. 15]`
  line
  line Orissa
  line
  line `Amendment of section 81.--In the principal Act, in section 81,--`
  line
  line `(a) for the words "or registering of any document" the words "registering or filing a true copy of`
  line `any document" shall be substituted;`
  line
  line `(b) for the words "or registers such document", the words "registers or files a true copy of such`
  line `document" shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Orissa Act 14 of 1989, s. 13]`
  line
  line Tripura--
  line
  line `Amendment of section 81.--For section 81 of the principal Act, the following shall be substituted,`
  line `namely:--`
  line
  line `"81. Every registering officer appointed under this Act, and every person employed in his office for`
  line `the purposes of this Act, who, being charged with the checking, endorsing, reading, examining, copying,`
  line `translating, comparing, pasting a true copy, pasting a copy of the translation or registering of any`
  line `document presented or deposited under its provisions checks, endorses, reads, examines, copies,`
  line `translates, compares, pastes a true copy, pastes a copy of the translation or registers such document in a`
  line `manner which he knows or believes to be incorrect intending thereby to cause or knowing it to be likely`
  line `that he may thereby cause injury as defined in the Indian Penal Code, to any person, shall be punishable`
  line `with imprisonment for a term which may extend to seven years, or with fine, or with both."`
  line
  line `[Vide Tripura Act 7 of 1982, s. 14]`
obj_root_law_sections_81_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_82:
  sectionId (37700)
  sectionNo (82)
  orderNo 85
  title `Penalty for making false statements, delivering false copies or translations, false personation, and abetment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_82_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_82_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338&sectionId=37700&sectionno=82&orderno=85&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338
obj_root_law_sections_82_content:
  string
  line Whoever--
  line
  line `(a) intentionally makes any false statement, whether on oath or not, and whether it has been`
  line `recorded or not, before any officer acting in execution of this Act, in any proceeding or enquiry under`
  line `this Act; or`
  line
  line `(b) intentionally delivers to a registering officer, in any proceeding under section 19 or section 21,`
  line `a false copy or translation of a document, or a false copy of a map or plan; or`
  line
  line `(c) falsely personates another, and in such assumed character presents any document, or makes`
  line `any admission or statement, or causes any summons or commission to be issued, or does any other act`
  line `in any proceeding or enquiry under this Act; or`
  line
  line `(d) abets anything made punishable by this Act,`
  line
  line `shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to seven years, or with fine, or with`
  line both.
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENTS`
  line
  line Karnataka
  line
  line `Amendment of section 82.--In clause (b) of section 82 of the principal Act, the following the`
  line `words and figures "under section 19 or section 21", the words "under this Act or the rules made`
  line `thereunder" shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Karnataka Act 55 of 1976, s. 18]`
  line
  line `Insertion of new section 82A,-- After section 82 of the principal Act, the following section shall be`
  line `inserted namely:--`
  line
  line `"82A. Penalty in respect of deed writers.--Whoever contravenes the provisions of section 80B or`
  line `any term or condition of a licence granted under rules made under section 69, shall be punishable`
  line `with imprisonment which may extend to one month or with fine which may extend to two hundred`
  line `rupees or with both"]`
  line
  line `[Vide Karnataka Act 55 of 1976, s. 19]`
  line
  line Kerala
  line
  line `Amendment of section 82.--In clause (b) of section 82 of the principal Act, for the words and figures`
  line `"section 19 or section 21", the words "this Act or the rules made thereunder" shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `[Vide kerala Act 7 of 1968, s. 16]`
  line
  line Orissa
  line
  line `Amendment of section 82.-- In the principal Act, in clause (b) of section 82, for the words and`
  line `figures "section 19 or section 21", the words "this Act or the rules under thereunder" shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Orissa Act 14 of 1989, s. 14]`
  line
  line Tripura--
  line
  line `Amendment of Section 82.--For sub-section (b) of section 82 of the principal Act, the following shall`
  line `be substituted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"(b) intentionally delivers to a registering Officer, in any proceeding under this Act or the rules made`
  line `thereunder, a false copy or translation of a document, or a false copy of a map or plan; or"`
  line
  line `[Vide Tripura Act 7 of 1982, s. 15]`
obj_root_law_sections_82_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_83:
  sectionId (37682)
  sectionNo (83)
  orderNo 86
  title `Registering officers may commence prosecutions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_83_content
  footnotes `1. The words the "Branch Inspector-General of Sindh", omitted by the A.O. 1937.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338&sectionId=37682&sectionno=83&orderno=86&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338
obj_root_law_sections_83_content:
  string
  line `(1) A prosecution for any offence under`
  line `this Act coming to the knowledge of a registering officer in his official capacity may be commenced by or`
  line `with the permission of the Inspector-General, ^1*** the Registrar or the Sub-Registrar, in whose territories,`
  line `district or sub-district, as the case may be, the offence has been committed.`
  line
  line `(2) Offences punishable under this Act shall be triable by any Court or officer exercising powers not`
  line `less than those of a Magistrate of the second class.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENTS`
  line
  line Kerala
  line
  line `Insertion of new sections 83A and 83B.--After section 83 of the principal Act, the following`
  line `sections shall be inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"83A. Cancellation of registered documents in certain cases.--(1) If on enquiry by an officer in`
  line `the Registration Department not below the rank of the deputy Inspector General of Registration, it is`
  line `found that some one has falsely personated another, and in such assumed character presented, admitted`
  line `the execution and got registered any document by a registering officer and the existence of such a`
  line `document is detrimental to the interest of another person, the same shall be cancelled by the Inspector`
  line `General of Registration on application made to him in such form as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) If on an enquiry conducted by the District Collector suo motu or on the basis of a complaint`
  line `received by him, it is found that any Government land or land owned by a public sector undertaking, has`
  line `been transferred on the strength of a document which is got registered without following the procedure`
  line `prescribed in sub-section (3) of section 71, the District Collector may make recommendation to the`
  line `Inspector General of Registration to cancel the registration of such document.`
  line
  line `(3) On receipt of such recommendation from the District Collector, the Inspector General of`
  line `Registration shall have the authority to cancel the registration of such document after following such`
  line `procedure as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `83B. Appeal to Government from orders of the Inspector General of Registration.--Any person`
  line `aggrieved by an order of the Inspector General of Registration under section 83A, may prefer an appeal`
  line `before the Government within thirty days from the date of receipt of such order, and the Government`
  line `shall pass an order confirming, modifying or cancelling the order of the Inspector General of Registration`
  line `as they deem fit.".`
  line
  line `[Vide Kerala Act 31 of 2013, s. 4]`
obj_root_law_sections_84:
  sectionId (37683)
  sectionNo (84)
  orderNo 87
  title `Registering officers to be deemed public servants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_84_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_84_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338&sectionId=37683&sectionno=84&orderno=87&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338
obj_root_law_sections_84_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every registering officer appointed`
  line `under this Act shall be deemed to be a public servant public servant within the meaning of the Indian`
  line `Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
  line
  line `(2) Every person shall be legally bound to furnish information to such registering officer when`
  line `required by him to do so.`
  line
  line `(3) In section 228 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860), the words judicial proceeding shall be`
  line `deemed to include any proceeding under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_84_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_85:
  sectionId (37684)
  sectionNo (85)
  orderNo 88
  title `Destruction of unclaimed documents.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_85_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_85_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338&sectionId=37684&sectionno=85&orderno=88&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338
obj_root_law_sections_85_content:
  string
  line `Documents (other than wills) remaining unclaimed in`
  line `any registration office for a period exceeding two years may be destroyed.`
obj_root_law_sections_85_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_86:
  sectionId (37685)
  sectionNo (86)
  orderNo 89
  title `Registering officer not liable for thing bona fide done or refused in his official capacity.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_86_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_86_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338&sectionId=37685&sectionno=86&orderno=89&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338
obj_root_law_sections_86_content:
  string
  line No
  line `registering officer shall be liable to any suit, claim or demand by reason of anything in good faith done or`
  line `refused in his official capacity.`
obj_root_law_sections_86_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_87:
  sectionId (37686)
  sectionNo (87)
  orderNo 90
  title `Nothing so done invalidated by defect in appointment or procedure.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_87_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_87_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338&sectionId=37686&sectionno=87&orderno=90&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338
obj_root_law_sections_87_content:
  string
  line `Nothing done in good`
  line `faith pursuant to this Act or any Act hereby repealed, by any registering officer, shall be deemed invalid`
  line `merely by reason of any defect in his appointment or procedure.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line Orissa
  line
  line `Insertion of new section 87-A (Act 16 of 1908).-- After section 87 of the Indian Registration Act,`
  line `1908 (16 of 1908) (hereinafter referred to as the principal Act), the following new section shall be`
  line `inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"87-A. Delegation of powers.--The State Government may, by order, delegate all or any of the`
  line `powers conferred on them under this Act to the Inspector-General of Registration, who shall exercise the`
  line `same subject to such restrictions and conditions as the State Government may impose and they may in`
  line `like manner withdraw any power so delegated."`
  line
  line `[Vide Orissa Act 7 of 1964, s. 2]`
obj_root_law_sections_87_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_88:
  sectionId (37687)
  sectionNo (88)
  orderNo 91
  title `88. Registration of documents executed by Government officers or certain public functionaries.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_88_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 39 of 1948, s. 5, for section 88.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338&sectionId=37687&sectionno=88&orderno=91&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338
obj_root_law_sections_88_content:
  string
  line `^1[88. Registration of documents executed by Government officers or certain public`
  line `functionaries.--(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, it shall not be necessary for,--`
  line
  line `(a) any officer of Government, or`
  line
  line `(b) any Administrator-General, Official Trustee or Official Assignee, or`
  line
  line `(c) the Sheriff, Receiver or Registrar of a High Court, or`
  line
  line `(d) the holder for the time being of such other public office as may be specified in a notification`
  line `in the Official Gazette issued in that behalf by the State Government,`
  line
  line `to appear in person or by agent at any registration office in any proceeding connected with the registration`
  line `of any instrument executed by him or in his favour, in his official capacity, or to sign as provided in`
  line `section 58.`
  line
  line `(2) Any instrument executed by or in favour of an officer of Government or any other person referred`
  line `to in sub-section (1) may be presented for registration in such manner as may be prescribed by rules made`
  line `under section 69.`
  line
  line `(3) The registering officer to whom any instrument is presented for registration under this section`
  line `may, if he thinks fit, refer to any Secretary to Government or to such officer of Government or other`
  line `person referred to in sub-section (1) for information respecting the same and, on being satisfied of the`
  line `execution thereof, shall register the instrument.]`
obj_root_law_sections_89:
  sectionId (37688)
  sectionNo (89)
  orderNo 92
  title `Copies of certain orders, certificates and instruments to be sent to registering officers and filed.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_89_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_89_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338&sectionId=37688&sectionno=89&orderno=92&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338
obj_root_law_sections_89_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every officer granting a loan under the Land Improvement Loans Act, 1883 (19 of 1883),`
  line `shall send a copy of his order to the registering officer within the local limits of whose jurisdiction the`
  line `whole or any part of the land to be improved or of the land to be granted as collateral security, is situate,`
  line `and such registering officer shall file the copy in his Book No. 1.`
  line
  line `(2) Every Court granting a certificate of sale of immovable property under the Code of Civil`
  line `Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), shall send a copy of such certificate to the registering officer within the local`
  line `limits of whose jurisdiction the whole or any part of the immovable property comprised in such certificate`
  line `is situate, and such officer shall file the copy in his Book No. 1.`
  line
  line `(3) Every officer granting a loan under the Agriculturists Loans Act, 1884 (12 of 1884), shall send a`
  line `copy of any instrument whereby immovable property is mortgaged for the purpose of securing the`
  line `repayment of the loan, and, if any such property is mortgaged for the same purpose in the order granting`
  line `the loan, a copy also or that order, to the registering officer within the local limits of whose jurisdiction`
  line `the whole or any part of the property so mortgaged is situate, and such registering officer shall file the`
  line `copy or copies as the case may be, in his Book No. 1.`
  line
  line `Exemption from Act`
  line
  line `(4) Every Revenue Officer granting a certificate of sale to the purchaser of immovable property sold`
  line `by public auction shall send a copy of the certificate to the registering officer within the local limits of`
  line `whose jurisdiction the whole or any part of the immovable property comprised in the certificate is situate,`
  line `and such officer shall file the copy in his Book No. 1.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENTS`
  line
  line Karnataka
  line
  line `Insertion of new section 89A.--After section 89 of the principal Act, the following section shall`
  line `be inserted namely:--`
  line
  line `89A. Power to make rules for filing of copies of documents.--(1) The State Government may`
  line `make rules for all purposes connected with the filing of true copies of documents in the appropriate`
  line `books under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for--`
  line
  line `(a) the furnishing of true copies of documents by the person presenting the documents for`
  line registration;
  line
  line `(b) the manner in which true copies of documents shall be prepared; and`
  line
  line `(c) the manner of filing of such copies.`
  line
  line `(3) All rules made under this section shall be published in the Official Gazette, and unless they`
  line `are expressed to come into force on a particular day, shall come into force on the day on which they`
  line `are so published.`
  line
  line `(4) Every rule made under this section shall be laid as soon as may be after it is made, before each`
  line `House of the State Legislature while it is in session for a total period of thirty days which may be`
  line `comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the`
  line `session in which it is so laid or the session immediately following, both Houses agree in making any`
  line `modification in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall`
  line `thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so however,`
  line `that any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything`
  line `previously done under that rule."`
  line
  line `[Vide Karnataka Act 55 of 1976, s. 20]`
  line
  line Kerala
  line
  line `Amendment of section 89.--In section 89 of the principal Act, --`
  line
  line `(a) sub-section (1) and (3) shall be omitted.`
  line
  line `(b) after sub-section (4), the following sub-sections shall be inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"(5) Every court passing`
  line
  line `(a) any decree or order creating, declaring, transferring, limiting or extinguishing and right, title`
  line `or interest to or in immovable property in favour of or of any person, or`
  line
  line `(b) an order for the attachment of immovable property or of the release of any immovable`
  line `property from attachment,`
  line
  line `Shall send a copy of such decree or order together with a memorandum describing the property, as far as`
  line `may be practicable in the manner required by section 21, to the registering officer within the local limits`
  line `of whose jurisdiction the whole or any part of the immovable property comprised in such decree or order`
  line `is situate, and such officer shall file the copy and memorandum in his Book No. 1.`
  line
  line `(6) Every officer issuing a written demand before the attachment of the immovable property of a`
  line `defaulter under the Revenue Recovery Act of the time being in force shall--`
  line
  line `(a) send a copy of such written demand together with a memorandum describing the property, as`
  line `far as may be practicable in the manner required by section 21; and`
  line
  line `(b) where such written demand is withdrawn or attachment of the property is lifted or the`
  line `property is sold and the sale is confirmed, send a memorandum indicating that fact and describing the`
  line `property, as far as may be practicable in the manner required by section 21,`
  line `to the registering officer within the local limits of whose jurisdiction the whole or any party of the`
  line `immovable property to which the written demand relates is situate and such registering officer shall fiel`
  line `the copy of the written demand and the memoranda I his Book No. 1.`
  line
  line `[Vide Kerala Act 7 of 1968, s. 17]`
  line
  line `Insertion of new section 89A.--After section 89 of the principal Act, the following section shall be`
  line `inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `89A. Power to make rules for filing of true copies of documents.--(1) The State Government`
  line `may make rules for all purposes connected with the filing of true copies of documents in the`
  line `appropriate books under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for--`
  line
  line `(a) the manner in which true copies of documents shall be prepared; and`
  line
  line `(b) the manner of filing such copies.`
  line
  line `(3) All rules made under this section shall be published in the Official Gazette and unless they are`
  line `expressed to come into force on a particular day, shall come into force on the day on which they are so`
  line published.
  line
  line `(4) Every rule made under this section shall be laid as soon as may be after it is made, before the`
  line `Legislative Assembly while it is in session for a total period of fourteen days which may be comprised in`
  line `one session or in two successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session in which it is so laid or`
  line `the session immediately following, the Legislative Assembly makes any modification in the rule or`
  line `decides that rule should not be made, the rule thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of`
  line `no effect as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification or annulment shall be without`
  line `prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that rule.`
  line
  line `[Vide kerala Act 7 of 1968, s. 18]`
  line
  line Orissa
  line
  line `Insertion of new section 89A (Act 16 of 1908).--After section 89 of the Indian Registration Act,`
  line `1908 (16 of 1908), the following new section shall be inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `89-A. Duty of Collector in proceedings under section 47-A of the Indian Stamps Act, 1899`
  line `(2 of 1899).--(1) It shall be the duty of the Collector, if he is satisfied during the proceedings, if any,`
  line `under section 47-A of the Indian Stamp Act, 1899 (2 of 1899) that the fees for registration paid under`
  line `this Act in respect of a document is in deficit, to determine in the course of such proceedings the`
  line `deficient amount of fees and to send a copy of the order made in the proceedings to the registering`
  line `officer for recovery of the said amount from the person liable to pay the deficient amount of stamp`
  line `duty under the said section; and all amounts recoverable as aforesaid may be recovered as arrears of`
  line `land revenue.`
  line
  line `(2) An order of the Collector under sub-section (1) shall be deemed to be an order made by the`
  line `Collector under section 47-A of the Indian Stamp Act, 1899 (2 of 1899) and shall be final subject to`
  line `the decision in appeal, if any, under sub-section (3) of the said section.`
  line
  line `[Vide Orissa Act 17 of 1966, s. 2]`
  line
  line Orissa
  line
  line `Insertion of new section 89.-- In the principal Act, after section 89-A, the following section shall`
  line `be inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `89-B. Power of State Government to make rules.--(1) The State Government may, by`
  line `notification in the official Gazette, make rules for all purposes connected with the filing of true copies`
  line `of documents in the appropriate books under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for,--`
  line
  line `(a) the furnishing of true copies of documents by the person presenting the documents for`
  line registration;
  line
  line `(b) the furnishing of true copies of documents by the person presenting the documents for`
  line registration;
  line `(c) the manner of filing such copies..`
  line
  line `[Vide Orissa Act 14 of 1989, s. 15]`
  line
  line Orissa
  line
  line `Amendment of section 89-A.--In Section 89-A of the principal Act, in Sub-section (1), for the`
  line `words and to send a copy of the order made in the proceedings to the registering officer for the recovery`
  line `of the said amount, the words and to recover the said amount of fees along with the deficient amount of`
  line `stamp duty shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Orissa Act 8 of 2002, s. 8]`
  line
  line Uttarakhand
  line
  line `Amendment of section 89./Sub-section (1), (2), (3) and (4) of section 89 of the Principal Act shall be substituted as follows; namely:-`
  line
  line `(1) Every officer granting a loan under the Land Improvement Loans Act, 1883 (XIX of 1883) shall send a copy of his order to the registering officer within the local limits of whose jurisdiction the whole, or any part of the land to be improved, or the land to be granted as collated security, is situate, and such registering officer shall take a similar action on it as taken on a document admitted to registration under sub-section (1) of section 61.`
  line
  line `(2) Every Court granting a certificate of sale of immovable property under the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (V of 1908), shall send a copy of such certificate to the registering officer within the local limits of whose jurisdiction the whole or any part of the immoveable property, comprised in such certificate, is situate and such officer shall take a similar action on it as taken on a document admitted to registration under sub-section (1) of section 61.`
  line
  line `(3) Every officer granting a loan under the Agriculturists Loans Act, 1884 (XII of 1884) shall send a copy of any instrument whereby immovable property is mortgaged for the purpose of securing the repayment of the loan and if any such property is mortgaged for the same purpose, in the order granting the loan, a copy, also the order, to the registering officer within the local limits of whose jurisdiction, the whole or any part of the property mortgaged is situate and such registering officer shall take a similar action on it as taken on a document admitted to registration under sub-section (1) of section 61.`
  line
  line `(4) Every Revenue Officer granting a certificate of sale to the purchase of immovable property, sold by public auction, shall send a copy of the certificate to the registering officer, within the local limits of whose jurisdiction, the whole or any part of the property comprised in the certificate is situate and such officer shall take a similar action on it as taken on a document admitted to registration under sub-section (1) of section 61.`
  line
  line `[Vide Uttarakhand Act 24 of 2019, s. 24].`
  line
  line Rajasthan
  line
  line `Amendment of section 89, Central Act XVI of 1908.-In section 89 of the principal Act, after sub-section (4), the following sub-section shall be added, namely:-`
  line
  line `(5) Every Bank granting a loan to an agriculturist for agricultural purposes, shall send within such time and in such manner as may be prescribed, a copy of any instrument whereby immovable property is mortgaged for the purpose of securing repayment of the loan, to the registering officer within the local limits of whose jurisdiction the whole or any part of the property so mortgaged is situate, and such registering officer shall file the copy in his Book No. 1.`
  line
  line `Explanation.- F or the purpose of sub-section (5),- (a) the expression ''every bank shall mean-`
  line
  line `(i) a banking company as defined in the Banking Regulation Act, 1949;`
  line
  line `(ii) the State Bank of India constituted under the State Bank of India Act, 1955;`
  line
  line `(iii) a subsidiary bank as defined in the State Bank of India (Subsidiary Bank) Act, 1959`
  line
  line `(iv) a corresponding new bank constituted under the Banking Companies (Acquisition and Transfer of Undertaking) Act, 1970;`
  line
  line `(v) a banking institution notified by the Central Government under section 51 of the Banking Regulation Act, 1949;br`
  line
  line `(vi) the Agricultural Refinance Corporation constituted under the Agricultural Re-finance Corporation Act, 1963;`
  line
  line `(vii) Agro-Industries Corporation ;`
  line
  line `(viii) Agricultural Finance Corporation Ltd.; a company incorporated under the Companies Act, 1956; and`
  line
  line `(ix) any other financial institution notified by the State government in the Official Gazette as a bank for the purpose of this Act.`
  line
  line `(b) the word agriculturist shall have the meaning assigned to it in sub-section ( 3) of section 5 of the Rajasthan Tenancy Act, 1955 (Rajasthan Act 3 of 1955).`
  line
  line `[Vide Rajasthan Act 16 of 1976, s. 5]`
  line
  line Gujarat
  line `Insertion of new sections 89A, 89B, 89C and 89D in XVI of 1908. -- In the principal Act, after section 89, the following sections shall be inserted, namely:-`
  line
  line `"89A. Copies of court decrees, attachment orders, etc., to be sent to Registering Officers and filed in registers. -- Every court passing,--`
  line
  line `(a) any decree or order creating, declaring, transferring, limiting or extinguishing any right, title or interest to or in immovable property in favour of any person, or`
  line
  line `(b) an order to interim attachment or attachment of immovable property or for the release of any immovable property from such attachment shall, in accordance with the rules made in this behalf,`
  line
  line `shall send a copy of such decree or order together with a memorandum describing the property as far as may be practicable, in the manner required by section 21, to the Registering Officer within the local limits of whose jurisdiction the whole or any part of the immovable property comprised in such decree or order, is situated, and such officer shall file the copy of the memorandum in his Book No 1:`
  line
  line `Provided that, where the immovable property is situated within the local limits of the jurisdiction of more than one Registering Officer, the procedure specified in clauses (a) and (b) of this sub-section shall be followed in respect of the property within the jurisdiction of each of such officer.`
  line
  line `(2) Every officer issuing a certificate of sale or a written demand before the attachment of the immovable property of a defaulter under the provisions of any law relating to Revenue Recovery for the time being in force including the Revenue Recovery Act, 1890, shall,-`
  line
  line `(a) send a copy of such certificate of sale or written demand together with a memorandum describing the property, as far as may be practicable, in the manner required by section 21;`
  line
  line `(b) where such written demand is withdrawn or attachment of property is lifted or the property sold and sale is confirmed, send a memorandum indicating that fact and describing that property, as far as may be practicable, in the manner required section 21, to the Registering Officer within the local limits of whose jurisdiction the whole or any part of the immovable property to which the written demand is situate, and such registering officer shall file a copy of the written demand and memorandum in his Book No 1:`
  line
  line `Provided that, where the immovable property is situate within the local limits of the jurisdiction of more than one Registering Officer, the procedure specified in clauses (a) and (b) of this sub-section shall be followed in respect of the property within the jurisdiction of each of such officers.`
  line
  line `"89B. Notice to be sent to Registering Officers by mortgag or in case of mortgage by depositing title deeds and provisions for compensation in favour of subsequent transferee."-- (l) Every person who has mortgaged immovable property by way of mortgage by depositing title deeds under clause (f) of section 58 of the Transfer of Property Act, 1882 (4 of 1882) shall, within 30 days from the date of mortgaged, file a notice of intimation of his having so mortgaged the property giving details of his name and address, name and address of mortgagee, date of mortgage, amount received under the mortgage, rate of interest payable, list of documents deposited, and description of the immovable property in the manner required by section 21, to the registering officer within the local limits of whose jurisdiction the whole or any part of the property is situated, and the said officer shall file the same in his cook No 1:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the property so mortgaged falls within the jurisdiction of more than one registering officer, the procedure specified in this sub-section shall be followed in respect of property within the jurisdiction of each of sum officers.`
  line
  line `(2) If, the person who has mortgaged the property as aforesaid fails to file a notice within 30 days as referred to in sub-section (1) before the registering officer or officers, as the case may be and enters into any transaction in relation to of affecting the immovable property which is subject matter of the mortgage, with a third party, such a transaction shall be void and the third party shall been titled to refund any amount paid by him together with interest at twelve per cent. from the date of payment and also to compensation for any damages suffered by him, from the transferor.`
  line
  line `(3) The amount recoverable by such transferee as specified in sub-section (2) shall be a charge on the interest of the mortgagor, in the mortgaged property:`
  line
  line `Provided that, nothing in this section shall apply to the instruments of agreement relating to mortgage by deposit of title deeds which are duly registered under the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `89C. Punishment for failure to file notice under section 89B. --Any person who fails to file a notice under section 89B to the registering officer along with fees, within the period specified in that section, shall be punished with imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than one years but which may be for a term which may be extend upto three years and shall also be liable to fine.`
  line
  line `89D. Power to make rules for filing of true copies of documents notices referred in sections 89A and 89B. --(1) The State Government in any, by notification in the Official Gazette, make rules for carrying out the purposes of section 89A and section 8 9B.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing powers, such rules may provide for,-`
  line
  line `(a) the manner in which notices or the copies of documents shall be prepared, and`
  line
  line `(b) the manner of filing of the notices or true copies.`
  line
  line `(3) All rules made under this section shall, be laid for not less than thirty days before the State Legislature as soon as possible after they are made and shall be subject to rescission by the State Legislature or to such modifications as the Strife Legislature may make, during the session in which they are so laid or the session immediately following.`
  line
  line `(4) Any rescission or modification so made by the State Legislature shall be published in the Official Gazette and shall thereupon take effect.`
  line
  line `[ Vide Gujarat Act 4 of 2020, s. 7 ]`
obj_root_law_sections_89_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_90:
  sectionId (37689)
  sectionNo (90)
  orderNo 93
  title `Exemption of certain documents executed by or in favour of Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_90_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_90_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338&sectionId=37689&sectionno=90&orderno=93&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338
obj_root_law_sections_90_content:
  string
  line `(1) Nothing`
  line `contained in this Act or in the Indian Registration Act, 1877 (3 of 1877), or in the Indian Registration Act, 1871 (8 of 1871), or in any Act thereby repealed, shall be deemed to require, or to have at any time`
  line `required, the registration of any of the following documents or maps, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) documents issued, received or attested by any officer engaged in making a settlement or`
  line `revision or settlement of land-revenue, and which form part of the records of such settlement; or`
  line
  line `(b) documents and maps issued, received or authenticated by any officer engaged on behalf of`
  line `Government in making or revising the survey of any land, and which form part of the record of such`
  line `survey; or`
  line
  line `(c) documents which, under any law for the time being in force, are filed periodically in any`
  line `revenue office by patwaris or other officers charged with the preparation of village records; or`
  line
  line `(d) sanads, inam, title-deeds and other documents purporting to be or to evidence grants or`
  line `assignments by Government of land or of any interest in land; or`
  line
  line `(e) notices given under section 74 or section 76 of the Bombay Land-Revenue Code, 1879, or`
  line `relinquishment of occupancy by occupants, or of alienated land by holders of such land.`
  line
  line `(2) All such documents and maps shall, for the purposes of sections 48 and 49, be deemed to have`
  line `been and to be registered in accordance with the provisions of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_90_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_91:
  sectionId (37690)
  sectionNo (91)
  orderNo 94
  title `Inspection and copies of such documents.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_91_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_91_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338&sectionId=37690&sectionno=91&orderno=94&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_43_00004_190816_1523340837338
obj_root_law_sections_91_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1)] Subject to such rules and the previous`
  line `payment of such fees as the ^2[`
  line `^3[State Government, by notification in the Official Gazette, prescribes in`
  line `this behalf], all documents and maps mentioned in section 90, clauses (a), (b), (c), and (e), and all`
  line `registers of the documents mentioned in clause (d), shall be open to the inspection of any person applying`
  line `to inspect the same, and, subject as aforesaid, copies of such documents shall be given to all persons`
  line `applying for such copies.`
  line
  line `^4[(2) Every rule prescribed under this sub-section or made under section 69 shall be laid, as soon as it`
  line `is made, before the State Legislature.]`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENTS`
  line
  line Tripura.--
  line
  line `Insertion of new section 91A.--After section 91 of the principal Act, the following new section shall`
  line `be inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `91-A. (1) The State Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, make rules for all`
  line `purposes connected with the pasting of true copies of documents in the appropriate Books under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for--`
  line
  line `(a) the furnishing of true copies of documents by the person presenting the document for registration;`
  line
  line `(b) the manner in which true copies of documents shall be prepared;`
  line
  line `(c) the manner in which the true copies of documents shall be compared with the original documents`
  line `after the same are admitted to registration ; and`
  line
  line `(d) the manner of pasting such copies.`
  line
  line `(3) Every rule made under this section shall be laid as soon as may be after it is made, before the`
  line `Legislative Assembly of Tripura, while it is in session for a total period of not less than fourteen days`
  line `which may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of`
  line `the session in which it is so laid or the successive sessions in which it is so laid or the successive sessions`
  line `aforesaid, the Legislative Assembly agrees in making any modification in the rule or the Legislative`
  line `Assembly agrees that the rule should not be made, the rule shall thereafter have effect only in such`
  line `modified form or be or no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification or`
  line `annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that rule.`
  line
  line `[Vide Tripura Act 7 of 1982, s. 16].`
obj_root_law_sections_91_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Section 91 renumbered as sub-section (1) thereof by Act 20 of 1983, s. 2 and Schedule.`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for "Provincial Government".`
  line
  line `3. Subs., ibid., for "State Government prescribes in this behalf".`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by Act 20 of 1983, s. 2 and Schedule (w.e.f. 15-3-1984).`
